1
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:52,218
SPONGE.
A LITTLE QUICKER.

2
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:58,224
VITALS STABLE AND HOLDING.

3
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:13,490
CLOSE HER UP, WILL YOU ?

4
00:01:22,499 --> 00:01:24,501
[ Indistinct Announcement
Over P.A. ]

5
00:01:24,501 --> 00:01:26,503
DAVID ?

6
00:01:26,619 --> 00:01:30,623
THERE HAS BEEN A TRAIN CRASH
OUTSIDE SANTA BARBARA.

7
00:01:30,623 --> 00:01:34,126
THEY'RE FLYING
AN AORTAL TRAUMA HERE NOW.

8
00:01:35,628 --> 00:01:39,632
HOW CAN I ASK YOU THIS,
DAVID ?

9
00:01:39,632 --> 00:01:41,634
[ Sighs ]

10
00:01:44,637 --> 00:01:47,139
I CAN DO IT, BLAKE.

11
00:01:57,283 --> 00:01:58,784
[ Woman ]
IS HE CRAZY, JASMINE ?

12
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:01,787
HE'S BEEN ON HIS FEET
FOR 14 HOURS.

13
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:05,291
CHLOE, IT'S BEEN THIS WAY
SINCE LESLIE DIED.

14
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:07,293
LOSING HIMSELF
IN HIS WORK, POOR THING.

15
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:09,662
THIS IS GETTING
A LITTLE RECKLESS, DON'T YOU THINK ?

16
00:02:09,662 --> 00:02:12,164
I DON'T THINK
HE HAS A CHOICE.

17
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:15,801
HANG ON A SECOND, JASMINE.
IT'S NOT LIKE HE HAS TO DO IT.

18
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:18,304
WELL, WHO ELSE
AT LOMA VISTA CAN DO IT ?

19
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:22,057
- WHO ELSE CAN DO
WHAT DAVID CAN DO ? - TRY LONNIE WALSH--

20
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:24,927
AND HE WOULDN'T EXPECT
TO BE KNIGHTED FOR IT.

21
00:02:24,928 --> 00:02:26,930
BLAKE, I CAN HANDLE
THAT TRANSPLANT.

22
00:02:26,930 --> 00:02:29,933
WE NEED SOMEBODY
WITH THE RIGHT KIND OF EXPERIENCE, LONNIE.

23
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:31,935
EVEN IF HE'S FALLING ASLEEP
ON HIS FEET ?

24
00:02:31,935 --> 00:02:33,937
IT'S A COMPLICATED
PROCEDURE, LONNIE.

25
00:02:34,437 --> 00:02:37,440
<i>WHY DON'T YOU OBSERVE ?</i>
<i>EXCUSE ME, MISS.</i>

26
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,575
...FRESH OUT
OF MEDICAL SCHOOL. <i>NO, YOU'RE NOT, LONNIE.</i>

27
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:42,829
YOU'RE A GOOD DOCTOR,
BUT YOU'RE NOT DAVID RAVELL.

28
00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:46,582
MISS ?

29
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:48,585
MISS ?

30
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:51,087
[ Woman #2 ]  HE WILL BE
HELD PERSONALLY RESPONSIBLE...

31
00:02:51,454 --> 00:02:53,456
<i>SHOULD ANYTHING GO WRONG</i>
<i>DURING THIS OPERATION.</i>

32
00:02:53,456 --> 00:02:57,209
<i>[ TV Continues,</i>
<i>Indistinct ]</i>

33
00:02:57,343 --> 00:02:59,845
YOU SEE THAT ?

34
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:01,848
<i>[ Woman #2 ]</i>
<i>...IS NOT UP TO HIS USUAL</i> <i>OLYMPIAN HEIGHTS...</i>

35
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,850
<i>OF SURGICAL SKILL.</i>

36
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:06,852
<i>HE COMPLAINED</i>
<i>OF DIZZINESS THIS MORNING.</i> <i>THAT SORT OF THING.</i>

37
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:08,855
- <i>DO YOU UNDERSTAND ?</i>
<i>- DO YOU WANT TO HEAR</i> <i>WHAT I HAVE IN MIND...</i>

38
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,357
FOR THE FAMOUS
DR. DAVID RAVELL ?

39
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:14,860
[ TV Announcer ]
A REASON TO LOVE WILL CONTINUE AFTER THESE MESSAGES.

40
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:17,480
SKIM, RIGHT ?

41
00:03:19,482 --> 00:03:21,484
HALF A PACK ?

42
00:03:23,987 --> 00:03:26,489
YOU KNOW,
THAT'S REALLY FATTY.

43
00:03:26,489 --> 00:03:28,491
[ Whispering ]
OUR COOK USES JUNK.

44
00:03:28,491 --> 00:03:30,493
YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'T
RATHER TRY A TURKEY BURGER ?

45
00:03:30,493 --> 00:03:32,995
YOU SURE YOU WANT A TIP
WHEN I'M DONE ?

46
00:03:32,996 --> 00:03:35,882
YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT'S YOUR BODY.

47
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:38,751
<i>RIGHT ?</i>
<i>THAT'S RIGHT.</i> <i>GET OFF IT.</i>

48
00:03:38,751 --> 00:03:41,887
- WESLEY !
- OH, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

49
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:45,141
I'VE TOLD HIM
THE SAME THING, MA'AM.

50
00:03:45,258 --> 00:03:46,759
THANKS FOR THE SUGGESTION.

51
00:03:48,144 --> 00:03:50,646
NO PROBLEM.

52
00:04:01,157 --> 00:04:04,160
HI, GUYS.
HERE YOU GO.

53
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,911
- HELLO, BETTY.
- HI, ROY.

54
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:08,915
- YOU'RE LOOKING GOOD.
- <i>[ Betty ]</i> <i>YOU'RE SWEET.</i>

55
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:12,418
HEY, YOU KNOW, I REALLY
ENJOYED YOUR EDITORIAL THIS MORNING.

56
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:14,420
WELL, THANK YOU.
I APPRECIATE IT.

57
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,422
I WAS REALLY TRYING
TO GET THE WHOLE HISTORY...

58
00:04:16,422 --> 00:04:18,924
OF THE EPISCOPALIAN CHURCH.
OH, IT WAS GREAT.

59
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:20,927
REALLY, IT JUST
PUT THE WHOLE IDEA...

60
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:24,430
OF THE CHURCH BAKE SALE
IN PERSPECTIVE.

61
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:27,433
<i>SOME PEOPLE LIKE</i>
<i>TO READ MORE THAN</i> <i>JUST THE CLASSIFIEDS.</i>

62
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:30,436
SO, SHERIFF,
HOW IS EVERYTHING ?

63
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:32,438
YOU KNOW, THE USUAL--

64
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:34,440
KEEPING THE WORLD SAFE.

65
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:37,443
- I MEANT YOUR FOOD.
- [ Laughing ]

66
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:44,450
HMM !

67
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:51,457
[ Whispering ]
SHE'S COMING.  SHE'S COMING.

68
00:04:51,824 --> 00:04:53,959
- [ Together ]
SURPRISE ! - OH !

69
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:57,463
HAPPY BIRTHDAY !

70
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,466
WHERE'D YOU GET IT ?
THAT'S SO EMBARRASSING.

71
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:03,335
- ON THE GODDAMN INTERNET,
WHERE ELSE ? - COME ON, POSE WITH HIM, BETTY.

72
00:05:03,336 --> 00:05:07,840
OKAY.
[ Laughs ]

73
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:13,479
A LITTLE SOMETHING
FOR THOSE NURSING CLASSES YOU BEEN WANTING TO TAKE.

74
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:16,732
BUT KEEP PUTTING OFF,
THANKS TO A CERTAIN HUSBAND WE WON'T MENTION.

75
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:18,735
- OH, YOU GUYS, I CAN'T.
- TAKE IT.

76
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:21,604
I CAN'T.
BETTY.

77
00:05:26,609 --> 00:05:29,561
[ Whispering ]
THANKS, YOU GUYS.

78
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:31,280
[ Man ]
YOU'VE REACHED SIZEMORE MOTORS,

79
00:05:31,781 --> 00:05:34,784
HOME OF THE BEST
SELECTION OF USED CARS IN THE BIG SPRINGS-FAIR OAKS AREA.

80
00:05:35,284 --> 00:05:37,286
WE CAN'T COME TO THE PHONE
RIGHT NOW,

81
00:05:37,286 --> 00:05:39,288
'CAUSE WE'RE OUT MAKING A SALE,
SO LEAVE US A MESSAGE. <i>[ Springs Creaking ]</i>

82
00:05:39,288 --> 00:05:43,292
BETTER YET, COME ON DOWN
AND STEAL ONE OF THESE BEAUTIES RIGHT OUT FROM UNDER US.

83
00:05:43,292 --> 00:05:45,294
COFFEE'S ALWAYS ON.
[ Machine Beeps ] [ Moaning ]

84
00:05:45,294 --> 00:05:49,298
[ Betty's Voice ]
HI, DEL.  IT'S ME. I GUESS YOU'RE BUSY,

85
00:05:49,298 --> 00:05:53,802
BUT I WANTED TO KNOW
IF I COULD TAKE ONE OF THE NEW BUICKS TONIGHT.

86
00:05:53,803 --> 00:05:55,805
[ Groans ]
[ Moans, Groans ]

87
00:05:55,805 --> 00:05:58,808
[ Sharp Groan ]

88
00:05:58,808 --> 00:06:02,061
SO CALL ME, UM--
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

89
00:06:02,061 --> 00:06:04,563
OH, UH, HI.
HANG ON A SECOND THERE, BABY.

90
00:06:05,064 --> 00:06:07,066
YOU'RE THERE.
WHAT DO YOU NEED ONE OF THE NEW BUICKS FOR ?

91
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:09,068
YOU SOUND OUT OF BREATH.

92
00:06:09,068 --> 00:06:12,071
[ Del ]
I RAN BACK IN TO GET THE PHONE.

93
00:06:12,071 --> 00:06:14,573
OH, WELL, UM--
[ Whispering ] JOYCE.  JOYCE.

94
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:16,458
SUE ANN IS TAKING ME OUT,

95
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:19,211
AND, UH, I JUST THOUGHT
IT MIGHT ME NICE...

96
00:06:19,212 --> 00:06:22,215
TO GO IN A NEW CAR.

97
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:26,719
- WHAT WAS THAT ?
- NOTHING. YOU KNOW, IT'S BUSY HERE.

98
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:29,221
WELL--
YOU DON'T NEED A LeSABRE TO GO OUT WITH SUE ANN.

99
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:33,226
- I DON'T <i>NEED</i> ONE, BUT--
- TAKE THE BLUE CORSICA.

100
00:06:56,365 --> 00:06:59,868
WELL, ONCE HE DUMPS HER,
WE WILL.  RIGHT. <i>[ Door Opening ]</i>

101
00:07:00,369 --> 00:07:02,371
OH.  HOLD ON A SECOND.

102
00:07:02,371 --> 00:07:06,875
HE'S OUT PRICING BANNERS,
BUT I DON'T EXPECT HIM BACK. OH.

103
00:07:06,876 --> 00:07:09,879
BANNERS ?
YOU KNOW, FLAGS AND SHIT.

104
00:07:10,379 --> 00:07:12,381
FOR A LIVELIER LOOK,
HE SAID.

105
00:07:12,381 --> 00:07:15,133
- OH.
- OH !

106
00:07:15,134 --> 00:07:17,136
IT'S A SHAME
ABOUT THE LeSABRES.

107
00:07:17,637 --> 00:07:20,640
- THEY'RE A REAL SWEET RIDE.
- YEAH.

108
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,142
HOW ARE THINGS
AT THE TIP TOP ?

109
00:07:23,142 --> 00:07:25,644
OH, THEY'RE FINE.

110
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:28,648
YEAH, FINE.

111
00:07:28,648 --> 00:07:32,034
YOU, UH--
YOU EVER MISS IT ?

112
00:07:32,034 --> 00:07:34,036
YOU... MUST BE KIDDIN'.

113
00:07:34,036 --> 00:07:36,538
OH.  YEAH.
[ Laughs ]

114
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:39,041
OKAY.

115
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:42,044
HI.  YEAH.
YEAH, MM-HMM.

116
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:44,546
<i>[ Whispering ]</i>
<i>THAT'S HIS WIFE.</i>

117
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,552
<i>THAT'S WHAT I SAID.</i>
<i>THAT'S WHAT I WAS</i> <i>TALKING--</i>

118
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:52,054
<i>YEAH, I WAS TALKING</i>
<i>ABOUT THAT.</i>

119
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:54,306
<i>ANYWAY, SO I WAS THINKING</i>
<i>EASTER, 'CAUSE...</i>

120
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:57,309
<i>I JUST FUCKING</i>
<i>LOVE PASTELS.</i>

121
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:26,839
HI.
DID YOU WATCH IT YET ? HI.

122
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:30,843
I SURE DID.
IF THAT MAN GOT ANY BETTER LOOKING,

123
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:33,346
IT WOULD BE A CRIME
OF SOME SORT.

124
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:35,848
I KNOW.

125
00:08:35,848 --> 00:08:39,852
OKAY, YOU READY ?
I'VE GOT A SURPRISE FOR TONIGHT.

126
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:42,354
WE'RE GOING TO THE STARLIGHT
IN STYLE.

127
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:44,607
OH, BETTY.
OKAY, I'LL GIVE YOU A HINT.

128
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:48,611
YOU SQUINT YOUR EYES
AND IT LOOKS JUST LIKE A JAGUAR.

129
00:08:48,611 --> 00:08:52,114
I AM SO SORRY.
I WAS GOING TO CALL YOU.

130
00:08:52,114 --> 00:08:56,118
LARRY'S GOT A LODGE MEETING.
THERE'S NO WAY I CAN GET A SITTER THIS FAST.

131
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:59,121
I FEEL AWFUL.
THAT'S OKAY.

132
00:08:59,121 --> 00:09:01,123
MAYBE NEXT WEEK WE CAN
GO BOWLING OR-- YEAH.

133
00:09:01,123 --> 00:09:03,125
THAT WOULD BE GREAT.
YEAH.

134
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:05,627
THAT'D BE GREAT.

135
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,630
WELL, THANKS.

136
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:09,632
OKAY, WELL,
HAVE A HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

137
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:11,884
OKAY ?
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

138
00:09:11,884 --> 00:09:16,355
I'D BETTER...
GO START DINNER.

139
00:09:19,425 --> 00:09:21,927
OKAY, HERE WE GO.

140
00:09:21,928 --> 00:09:23,930
MM-HMM.

141
00:09:24,430 --> 00:09:26,432
YOU SURE YOU DON'T
WANT ANY SALAD ?

142
00:09:26,432 --> 00:09:28,934
NO, I DON'T WANT
ANY SALAD. OKAY.

143
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:30,937
OKAY.
WHAT WAS ALL THAT SHIT ON THE PHONE...

144
00:09:30,937 --> 00:09:32,939
ABOUT THE BUICKS ?
HERE YOU GO. I TOLD YOU.

145
00:09:33,439 --> 00:09:35,441
SUE ANN WAS GOING
TO TAKE ME OUT, BUT--

146
00:09:35,441 --> 00:09:37,443
WHAT, SHE'S
NOT COMFORTABLE IN A CORSICA ?

147
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:40,580
<i>IT'S GOT AIR.</i>
<i>IT'S GOT LEATHER.</i>

148
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:43,332
ACTUALLY, I'M GLAD
YOU'RE GOING OUT TONIGHT.

149
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:45,834
OH, YEAH ?
<i>YEAH.  I GOT SOMETHING</i> <i>GOING ON.</i>

150
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:49,839
SOME SERIOUS CLIENTS--
WITH REAL POTENTIAL.

151
00:09:49,839 --> 00:09:51,841
OH.

152
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:54,710
SO, UM,

153
00:09:54,710 --> 00:09:57,713
WHO ARE THESE CLIENTS ?

154
00:09:58,214 --> 00:10:00,216
COUPLE OF GUYS IN
FROM OUT OF TOWN.

155
00:10:00,216 --> 00:10:02,218
THEY WANT TO SEE
THE NEW LeSABRES.

156
00:10:02,218 --> 00:10:04,470
NEW LeSABRES ?

157
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:07,973
JESUS CHRIST.
LOOK AT THESE GUYS.

158
00:10:07,974 --> 00:10:09,976
WHO ARE THEY FUCKIN' ?

159
00:10:09,976 --> 00:10:12,979
YOU KNOW THESE ACTORS
ARE MAINLY MODELS-- WHICH ARE MAINLY FAGGOTS.

160
00:10:13,479 --> 00:10:15,481
- OH ?
- [ Scoffs ]

161
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:23,489
<i>AND THE REST</i>
<i>ARE ASSHOLES.</i>

162
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:28,127
KNOW WHAT BUGS ME MOST
ABOUT THOSE SOAPS ?

163
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:30,746
- HMM ?
- IT'S PEOPLE WITH NO LIVES...

164
00:10:30,746 --> 00:10:34,249
[ Together ]
WATCHING OTHER PEOPLE'S FAKE LIVES.

165
00:10:35,751 --> 00:10:37,753
YEAH, WELL,

166
00:10:37,753 --> 00:10:40,756
NOTHIN' LIKE WATCHING
THE TENPINS FALL, HUH ?

167
00:10:40,756 --> 00:10:43,258
HEY, THAT'S A SKILL.

168
00:10:43,259 --> 00:10:45,761
THEY'RE TRYING
TO GET THAT IN THE OLYMPIC GAMES.

169
00:10:49,765 --> 00:10:52,267
ALL RIGHT.
I'M GONNA GO OUT. CLEAN THIS SHIT UP.

170
00:11:29,305 --> 00:11:31,307
I TOLD HIM MY CAR'S
IN THE SHOP.

171
00:11:31,307 --> 00:11:35,311
- HE SAID HE'D BE HAPPY TO GIVE
ME A RIDE HOME TOMORROW. - YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.

172
00:11:35,811 --> 00:11:37,813
<i>[ Chloe ]</i>
<i>TELL ME SOMETHING</i> <i>I DON'T KNOW.</i>

173
00:11:37,813 --> 00:11:40,315
[ Lonnie ]
I'VE GOT SOME SPECIAL PLANS FOR YOU AND I--

174
00:11:40,816 --> 00:11:43,318
THINGS COMING UP
IN THE NEAR FUTURE I THINK YOU'LL LIKE.

175
00:11:43,819 --> 00:11:45,320
HMM.  MM-HMM.

176
00:11:45,321 --> 00:11:49,325
<i>[ Car Approaching ]</i>

177
00:11:56,832 --> 00:11:58,834
ALL I'M SAYING IS,
THEIR OFFENCE SUCKS.

178
00:12:08,844 --> 00:12:10,846
YOU CAN HAVE THE BEST
DAMN RUNNING BACKS IN THE WORLD,

179
00:12:10,846 --> 00:12:14,349
BUT SOMEBODY'S
STILL GOTTA BLOCK FOR THEM. YOU'RE 100% RIGHT THERE.

180
00:12:16,852 --> 00:12:19,354
<i>I TOLD MY WIFE TO CLEAN</i>
<i>THIS SHIT UP BEFORE</i> <i>SHE WENT OUT.</i>

181
00:12:19,355 --> 00:12:21,357
LET'S HAVE SOME MUSIC.

182
00:12:23,359 --> 00:12:27,863
♪ [ Blues-Jazz ]
YOU GUYS LIKE MUSIC ?

183
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:34,370
[ David ]
...TO SEE HOW FAST THIS BEAUTY WILL GO, THOUGH.

184
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:38,874
I GUESS SOMEHOW
THAT SPEED HELPS ME FORGET THE PAST.

185
00:12:38,874 --> 00:12:40,876
LISTEN, DAVID.

186
00:12:40,876 --> 00:12:43,378
I KNOW I'VE SAID IT BEFORE,
BUT I WANT TO TELL YOU AGAIN...

187
00:12:43,379 --> 00:12:45,881
HOW SORRY I AM
ABOUT YOUR WIFE.

188
00:12:46,382 --> 00:12:48,384
- WELL, WE SHOULD PROBABLY--
- LET'S NOT GO.

189
00:12:48,884 --> 00:12:51,386
NOT YET.

190
00:12:51,387 --> 00:12:53,889
YOU GOT A FINE ONE
RIGHT HERE.

191
00:12:53,889 --> 00:12:55,891
YOUR WIFE
IS VERY ATTRACTIVE, DEL.

192
00:12:56,392 --> 00:13:00,896
- HAVE I SEEN HER BEFORE ?
- IF YOU ATE AT THE TIP TOP, YOU DID.

193
00:13:00,896 --> 00:13:04,399
OH, YEAH.
YEAH-- THE COFFEE.

194
00:13:06,402 --> 00:13:09,538
YEAH.  BETTY POURS
A MEAN CUP.

195
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:12,040
LET'S SIT IN HERE.

196
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:15,044
[ Chloe ]
WHEN SKIPPER DIED, IT HURT SO BAD...

197
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:19,364
I JUST WANTED
THE WORLD TO GO AWAY.

198
00:13:19,498 --> 00:13:22,250
TO A SUCCESSFUL TRANSACTION.

199
00:13:26,755 --> 00:13:29,257
[ Chloe ]
WE ARE WHERE WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE.

200
00:13:29,758 --> 00:13:32,761
AND IF YOU FEEL SOMETHING...

201
00:13:32,761 --> 00:13:34,763
FOR SOMEONE, YOU SHOULD--

202
00:13:38,767 --> 00:13:42,270
[ Material Ripping ]
PLEASE !

203
00:13:46,775 --> 00:13:50,278
IT'S NOT THAT I DON'T
FIND YOU ATTRACTIVE.

204
00:13:50,279 --> 00:13:52,281
I'M JUST NOT READY.

205
00:13:52,281 --> 00:13:55,534
NO, HE'S NOT READY.

206
00:13:55,534 --> 00:13:59,538
NICE PLACE YOU GOT HERE, DEL.
REAL COMFORTABLE.

207
00:13:59,538 --> 00:14:01,540
SWEET LITTLE TOWN,
FAIR OAKS.

208
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:03,625
DO YOU LIKE IT ?
<i>WHAT, ARE YOU</i> <i>KIDDING ME ?</i>

209
00:14:04,126 --> 00:14:06,628
