00:53:04,264 --> 00:53:07,767
- YOU SOUND LIKE
A FUCKIN' MADMAN. - <i>ARE YOU AN AMERICAN, WESLEY ?</i>

827
00:53:07,767 --> 00:53:12,772
YES, I'M AN AMERICAN.
AND NO, I'M NOT GOING TO THE FUCKIN' BLAND CANYON.

828
00:53:14,274 --> 00:53:17,277
♪ [ Radio: Country ]

829
00:53:19,279 --> 00:53:22,782
[ Coyotes Howling ]

830
00:53:22,782 --> 00:53:25,284
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE MISSING.

831
00:53:27,287 --> 00:53:29,539
ASSHOLE.

832
00:53:29,539 --> 00:53:32,291
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

833
00:53:32,292 --> 00:53:34,911
- WHAT'S UP ?
- MR. CAMPBELL ?

834
00:53:34,911 --> 00:53:39,165
- HUH ?
- IS THIS MUTUAL LIFE INSURANCE ?

835
00:53:39,165 --> 00:53:43,169
- <i>HELLO ?  HELLO !</i>
<i>- YEAH, YEAH.</i> <i>THIS IS DWIGHT CAMPBELL.</i>

836
00:53:43,169 --> 00:53:47,673
MY NAME'S SUE ANN ROGERS.
I'M BETTY SIZEMORE'S FRIEND. I'VE HEARD FROM HER.

837
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:50,560
YEAH ?
SHE WAS AT A BAR IN ARIZONA.

838
00:53:50,560 --> 00:53:52,929
♪ [ Music Swells ]

839
00:53:52,929 --> 00:54:01,437
[ Woman ]
♪ DON'T YOU KNOW ♪

840
00:54:01,438 --> 00:54:06,443
♪ I WAS YOURS
FROM THE VERY DAY ♪

841
00:54:06,443 --> 00:54:12,449
♪ THAT YOU HAPPENED
TO COME MY WAY ♪

842
00:54:12,449 --> 00:54:19,456
♪ CAN'T YOU SEE ♪

843
00:54:19,956 --> 00:54:24,961
♪ I'M UNDER YOUR SPELL ♪

844
00:54:24,961 --> 00:54:31,467
♪ BY THE LOOK IN MY EYES ♪

845
00:54:31,468 --> 00:54:33,470
♪ CAN'T YOU TELL ♪

846
00:54:33,470 --> 00:54:36,473
♪ CAN'T YOU TELL ♪

847
00:54:36,473 --> 00:54:44,981
♪ NOW, DON'T YOU KNOW ♪

848
00:54:44,981 --> 00:54:46,983
♪ EVERY BEAT OF MY HEART ♪
[ Wesley ] THANK YOU.

849
00:54:46,983 --> 00:54:51,487
♪ KEEPS CRYING OUT ♪

850
00:54:51,488 --> 00:54:54,491
- WHAT THE FUCK ?
- <i>♪ I WANT YOU SO ♪</i>

851
00:54:54,491 --> 00:54:57,994
- [ Horn Honks ]
- <i>♪ DON'T YOU KNOW ♪</i>

852
00:54:57,994 --> 00:55:00,997
- COME HERE !
- <i>♪ [ Ends ]</i>

853
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:06,886
[ Coyotes Howling ]

854
00:55:12,392 --> 00:55:14,894
<i>[ Howling Continues ]</i>

855
00:55:18,398 --> 00:55:20,900
DID YOU HAVE
A GOOD TIME ?

856
00:55:20,900 --> 00:55:24,904
YOU MAKE A WISH ?
GET IN TOUCH WITH YOUR BLACKNESS ?

857
00:55:26,406 --> 00:55:28,408
FOUND YOUR BETTY.

858
00:55:28,408 --> 00:55:30,910
WELL, AT LEAST WHERE
SHE'S BEEN HANGING OUT.

859
00:55:31,411 --> 00:55:34,414
WHERE ?  WHERE IS SHE ?

860
00:55:34,414 --> 00:55:36,916
NOT TELLING YOU.
WHAT ?

861
00:55:36,916 --> 00:55:39,919
I'M NOT TELLING YOU
TILL YOU STRAIGHTEN OUT.

862
00:55:39,919 --> 00:55:44,423
DANCING AROUND LIKE FUCKIN'
BOJANGLES OUT THERE-- WHAT THE FUCK ?

863
00:55:44,424 --> 00:55:46,926
THIS SHIT'S GOTTA STOP,
AND I MEAN IT.

864
00:56:16,740 --> 00:56:18,742
DO YOU THINK WE SHOULD
GO IN AND SIT ?

865
00:56:18,742 --> 00:56:23,246
NO.  I WAS THINKING WE
COULD JUST STAY OUT HERE FOR A LITTLE WHILE...

866
00:56:23,246 --> 00:56:25,748
AND MINGLE
A LITTLE BIT. OKAY.

867
00:56:31,504 --> 00:56:34,006
GOOD TO SEE YOU.
WELL, I'M GLAD TO BE HERE.

868
00:56:34,007 --> 00:56:36,009
OH, SURE, ABSOLUTELY.

869
00:56:36,509 --> 00:56:38,511
LOOK WHO'S HERE.

870
00:56:39,012 --> 00:56:41,514
HMM ?
OVER THERE.

871
00:56:46,019 --> 00:56:48,654
WELL ?

872
00:56:50,156 --> 00:56:52,158
WHAT ARE YOU
WAITING FOR ?

873
00:56:52,158 --> 00:56:54,160
TALK TO HIM, HUH ?

874
00:56:54,160 --> 00:56:56,662
YOU CAME 1500 MILES
FOR THIS.

875
00:57:05,422 --> 00:57:07,424
[ Chuckles ]

876
00:57:22,939 --> 00:57:25,942
YOU'RE SERIOUS
ABOUT THIS. HE'S GOT HIS OWN COMPANY.

877
00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:28,945
I MEAN, HE'S THE GUY
YOU WANTED TO TELL.

878
00:57:28,945 --> 00:57:32,448
<i>[ Chattering, Indistinct ]</i>

879
00:57:32,949 --> 00:57:34,951
DO I KNOW YOU ?

880
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:38,571
OF COURSE.
[ Laughs ] DON'T YOU REMEMBER ?

881
00:57:38,571 --> 00:57:44,076
- I-I TAKE IT I SHOULD.
- SILLY.  IT'S ME.

882
00:57:46,079 --> 00:57:48,581
WE WERE ENGAGED.

883
00:57:48,581 --> 00:57:52,468
- YOU WERE ENGAGED.
- [ Chuckles ]

884
00:57:52,469 --> 00:57:54,471
I-I BEG YOUR PARDON ?

885
00:57:54,471 --> 00:57:59,476
LETTING YOU GO,
THAT WAS THE BIGGEST MISTAKE OF MY LIFE.

886
00:57:59,476 --> 00:58:02,729
AND IT'S A MISTAKE
I'VE HAD TO LIVE WITH FOR SIX YEARS,

887
00:58:02,729 --> 00:58:08,234
BUT I'VE PUT IT BEHIND ME NOW,
AND I JUST HOPE THAT YOU CAN PUT IT BEHIND YOU TOO.

888
00:58:09,736 --> 00:58:12,238
I'VE MISSED YOU.

889
00:58:12,739 --> 00:58:15,358
I'VE <i>MISSED</i> YOU, DAVID.

890
00:58:16,359 --> 00:58:18,494
[ Laughing ]

891
00:58:18,495 --> 00:58:20,997
THAT'S... VERY NICE.

892
00:58:20,997 --> 00:58:23,499
THAT WAS VERY GOOD.
I GREATLY APPRECIATE THAT.

893
00:58:23,500 --> 00:58:26,503
WOW.  THAT WAS--  WOW.
GOOD. [ Laughs ]

894
00:58:26,503 --> 00:58:29,255
THEY DAY I LEFT YOU,
I JUST DROVE AND DROVE.

895
00:58:29,255 --> 00:58:31,257
I DROVE ALL DAY
AND ALL THAT NIGHT.

896
00:58:31,758 --> 00:58:36,763
I JUST KEPT DRIVING.
I STOPPED AT THIS OLD COUNTRY CHURCH,

897
00:58:36,763 --> 00:58:40,266
AND THE PASTOR LET ME IN,
AND I SAT--

898
00:58:40,266 --> 00:58:43,269
IN THE VERY FIRST PEW,
WHERE WE WOULD'VE SAT ON OUR WEDDING DAY.

899
00:58:44,771 --> 00:58:47,273
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I REMEMBERED THAT.

900
00:58:47,273 --> 00:58:49,275
ALTHOUGH I SHOULD.
I WROTE IT.

901
00:58:49,275 --> 00:58:52,778
BUT THAT WAS SEVEN YEARS AGO,
AND YOU'RE QUOTING IT VERBATIM.

902
00:58:52,779 --> 00:58:56,783
I'M... FLATTERED,
I THINK.

903
00:58:56,783 --> 00:58:59,786
- OR FRIGHTENED.
- [ Laughs ]

904
00:58:59,786 --> 00:59:03,790
WHAT'S YOUR NAME ?
BETTY SIZEMORE. WHAT'D YOU WRITE ?

905
00:59:03,790 --> 00:59:06,292
I'M LYLA BRANCH.
I'M THE PRODUCER.

906
00:59:06,793 --> 00:59:10,046
UH-HUH.
I HAVE TO ADMIT, YOU HAD ME GOING THERE.

907
00:59:10,046 --> 00:59:13,049
[ Laughing ]
YOU'RE BETTER THAN MOST OF THEM ANYWAY.

908
00:59:13,049 --> 00:59:15,051
YEAH.
DO YOU HAVE A HEAD SHOT ?

909
00:59:15,051 --> 00:59:18,170
WAIT A SECOND.
SO WHAT HAPPENS NEXT, BETTY ?

910
00:59:18,171 --> 00:59:20,673
ARE YOU SURE YOU--
WELL, WHY NOT ?

911
00:59:20,673 --> 00:59:23,175
WHAT--  WHAT DOES
HAPPEN NEXT, BETTY ?

912
00:59:23,176 --> 00:59:27,063
WELL, DAVID CAME OUT TO,
UH, DO HIS RESIDENCY,

913
00:59:27,063 --> 00:59:29,565
AND THEN HE MET LESLIE--
<i>NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.</i>

914
00:59:29,566 --> 00:59:33,570
WE KNOW ALL THAT.
WE WANT TO KNOW WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU, BETTY.

915
00:59:33,570 --> 00:59:38,324
OH.  OH.  WELL--

916
00:59:39,325 --> 00:59:41,827
I MARRIED A CAR SALESMAN.

917
00:59:41,828 --> 00:59:44,330
[ Laughs ]
REALLY ?

918
00:59:44,330 --> 00:59:48,834
YOU WERE--
YOU WERE DUMPED FOR A CAR SALESMAN, GEORGE.

919
00:59:48,835 --> 00:59:51,337
- WHY'D YOU CALL HIM
"GEORGE" ? - WHY DID I CALL HIM--

920
00:59:51,337 --> 00:59:54,340
YEAH, DAVID, <i>TELL US</i>
<i>ABOUT THE CAR SALESMAN.</i>

921
00:59:54,340 --> 00:59:58,344
OH, RIGHT, RIGHT.
WELL, YOU'RE, UM--

922
00:59:58,344 --> 01:00:01,847
YOU'RE TALKIN' ABOUT,
UH, FRED THERE.

923
01:00:02,348 --> 01:00:04,850
DEL.
DEL.  DEL.  YEAH.

924
01:00:04,851 --> 01:00:06,853
UH, DEL.
HE WAS AMAZING.

925
01:00:06,853 --> 01:00:09,856
OH, YEAH.
HE WAS, I MEAN, THIS GUY--

926
01:00:09,856 --> 01:00:14,360
TALK ABOUT SALESMEN,
HE COULD SELL ANYTHING TO ANYBODY...

927
01:00:14,360 --> 01:00:17,363
AT ANY TIME, AMAZING.
YOU KNOW DEL ?

928
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:20,366
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO TELL YOU THIS, BUT DEL AND I GO WAY BACK.

929
01:00:20,366 --> 01:00:23,369
WE WENT TO SCHOOL TOGETHER.
AS A MATTER OF FACT,

930
01:00:24,370 --> 01:00:26,372
HE SAVED MY LIFE.

931
01:00:26,372 --> 01:00:30,876
- OH, MY GOSH.
- LIKE, TWO MORE MINUTES IN THAT FREEZING-COLD WATER,

932
01:00:31,377 --> 01:00:34,380
AND I SWEAR TO GOD,
I WOULD'VE DROWNED, BUT--

933
01:00:37,884 --> 01:00:40,002
- DEL.
- [ Laughs ]

934
01:00:40,503 --> 01:00:44,006
DEL JUMPED IN AND HE
GRABBED ME AND HE JUST, HE PULLED ME OUT.

935
01:00:44,007 --> 01:00:46,009
- [ Laughs ]
- IT WAS AMAZING.

936
01:00:46,009 --> 01:00:50,013
PULLED HIM--
HOLD ON. I'M HAVING A MOMENT HERE.

937
01:00:50,013 --> 01:00:55,018
I LOST TOUCH WITH HIM
AFTER THAT, BUT... I STILL OWE HIM.

938
01:00:55,018 --> 01:01:00,023
HE NEVER SAID ANYTHING.
THAT IS UNBELIEVABLE.

939
01:01:00,023 --> 01:01:02,025
THAT'S FUNNY.
IT'S JUST WHAT I WAS THINKING.

940
01:01:02,025 --> 01:01:06,029
I KNOW !
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW MUCH IT HURT ME...

941
01:01:06,029 --> 01:01:09,782
TO HEAR THAT
YOU MARRIED HIM. OH, I'M SO SORRY.

942
01:01:09,782 --> 01:01:12,785
I TRIED TO TELL MYSELF,
AT FIRST, IT WAS FOR THE BEST,

943
01:01:12,785 --> 01:01:16,789
THAT THERE WAS SOME
SORT OF REASON FOR IT, BUT DEL ?

944
01:01:16,789 --> 01:01:20,292
I WAS YOUNG
AND-AND STUPID AND SCARED.

945
01:01:20,293 --> 01:01:24,297
- YOU NEVER EVEN
GAVE US A CHANCE. - I KNOW.

946
01:01:24,430 --> 01:01:29,435
I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW MANY TIMES I-I TELL MYSELF THAT SAME THING.

947
01:01:30,937 --> 01:01:35,942
[ Sobbing ]
I'M--  ARE YOU REALLY CRYING HERE ?

948
01:01:35,942 --> 01:01:38,444
I'M JUST--
I WAS KINDA PLAYING ALONG.

949
01:01:38,945 --> 01:01:41,697
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
GEORGE ?

950
01:01:43,199 --> 01:01:45,701
WHY DOES HE KEEP
CALLING YOU GEORGE ?

951
01:01:45,702 --> 01:01:47,704
I DON'T KNOW.

952
01:01:47,704 --> 01:01:52,325
<i>LISTEN, BETTY,</i>
<i>I'M SURE YOU'LL UNDERSTAND.</i>

953
01:01:52,325 --> 01:01:56,962
DAVID IS A VERY BUSY MAN,
SO WE REALLY HAVE TO GO.

954
01:01:56,963 --> 01:01:58,965
NOW.

955
01:01:58,965 --> 01:02:00,967
IT WAS A PLEASURE
MEETING YOU. BYE.

956
01:02:01,467 --> 01:02:04,470
WE GOTTA GET TO THIS,
UH, PREVIOUS ENGAGEMENT.

957
01:02:04,470 --> 01:02:06,472
BUT, UH--
OH.

958
01:02:06,472 --> 01:02:08,974
IT WAS GOOD.
IT WAS SO GREAT.

959
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:11,477
ALL RIGHT.

960
01:02:18,101 --> 01:02:22,605
UH, I WOULD BE HONORED
IF YOU'D JOIN US.

961
01:02:22,605 --> 01:02:25,608
WHAT... AN IDEA.

962
01:02:25,608 --> 01:02:28,611
I'M SURE YOU TWO
HAVE A LOT OF CATCHING UP TO DO,

963
01:02:28,611 --> 01:02:32,364
<i>DAVID.</i>
<i>YEAH ?</i>

964
01:02:33,366 --> 01:02:35,501
ALL RIGHT.

965
01:02:46,129 --> 01:02:48,631
THANK YOU.
HOLD ON A MINUTE.

966
01:02:48,631 --> 01:02:50,633
THANK YOU.

967
01:02:50,633 --> 01:02:52,635
HEY, THANKS, MAN.
I LOVE YOUR WORK.

968
01:02:52,635 --> 01:02:54,637
OH, THANK YOU.
THANKS A LOT.

969
01:02:54,637 --> 01:02:58,140
[ George ]
HEY, LOOK WHO'S HERE !

970
01:03:00,143 --> 01:03:02,395
WHAT'S LONNIE
DOING HERE ?

971
01:03:02,395 --> 01:03:05,398
- WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU ?
- LATE, AS USUAL.

972
01:03:05,898 --> 01:03:09,651
I KNOW.
WHY ARE YOU GUYS LEAVING ?

973
01:03:09,652 --> 01:03:13,656
- WE DID OUR 20 MINUTES.
- OH.  WHO'S THE SKIRT ?

974
01:03:15,658 --> 01:03:17,793
[ Laughing ]

975
01:03:17,794 --> 01:03:20,913
APPARENTLY, SOMEBODY
WHO DOESN'T LIKE TO BE REFERRED TO AS A "SKIRT."

976
01:03:20,913 --> 01:03:22,798
YOU !

977
01:03:22,799 --> 01:03:25,802
RELAX.  SHE DIDN'T EVEN
GET YOU THAT HARD.

978
01:03:26,169 --> 01:03:30,923
- DO I KNOW YOU ?
- NO, BUT I KNOW JUST WHO YOU ARE.

979
01:04:01,170 --> 01:04:04,173
THIS DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
THE KIND OF PLACE BETTY WOULD COME TO.

980
01:04:04,173 --> 01:04:06,175
MAYBE SHE HAD
TO GO TO THE BATHROOM.

981
01:04:06,175 --> 01:04:08,677
I MEAN, SHE DOES PEE,
DOESN'T SHE ?

982
01:04:08,678 --> 01:04:11,681
OR IS SHE
TOO POISED TO PEE ?

983
01:04:11,681 --> 01:04:14,183
HEY.  BE CAREFUL WITH THAT.

984
01:04:17,186 --> 01:04:20,189
<i>[ Door Squeaks, Closes ]</i>
<i>♪ [ Jukebox: Indistinct ]</i>

985
01:04:37,823 --> 01:04:39,825
WHAT CAN I GET YA ?

986
01:04:42,078 --> 01:04:44,580
WE'RE FEDERAL MARSHALS,
MA'AM.

987
01:04:45,081 --> 01:04:48,467
WE'RE LOOKIN' FOR
THIS YOUNG LADY.

988
01:04:50,469 --> 01:04:53,472
I HAVEN'T SEEN HER.

989
01:04:53,472 --> 01:04:55,974
YOU SURE HAVE !

990
01:04:55,975 --> 01:04:59,345
- SHUT UP, MERLE.
- BETTY ! HER NAME IS BETTY.

991
01:04:59,345 --> 01:05:02,348
I'VE NEVER SEEN
THAT WOMAN BEFORE, AND NEITHER HAS MERLE.

992
01:05:02,348 --> 01:05:07,853
HE DRINKS TOO MUCH.
AND DON'T TRY TO TELL ME YOU'RE COPS.

993
01:05:07,853 --> 01:05:12,357
I WAS MARRIED TO A COP
FOR NINE YEARS. YOU'RE NOT COPS.

994
01:05:12,358 --> 01:05:14,993
- MOTHERFUCK !
- <i>[ Crash ]</i>

995
01:05:14,994 --> 01:05:17,997
[ Merle ]
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN' ? SHUT UP !

996
01:05:17,997 --> 01:05:21,500
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
FORTHCOMING WITH US.

997
01:05:22,535 --> 01:05:26,539
SO LYLA'S VERY NICE.

998
01:05:26,539 --> 01:05:29,041
REALLY TALL.

999
01:05:30,543 --> 01:05:33,045
YES, SHE IS.

1000
01:05:33,045 --> 01:05:38,050
YOU KNOW, SHE SAID
SHE THOUGHT THAT I WAS CHARMING AND RELENTLESS.

1001
01:05:38,551 --> 01:05:43,556
SHE SAID THAT I WOULD
GO FAR IN THIS TOWN.

1002
01:05:43,556 --> 01:05:48,060
OH, AND SHE SAID THAT,
UNLIKE MOST CHARMING AND RELENTLESS PEOPLE SHE KNEW,

1003
01:05:48,060 --> 01:05:50,062
SHE LIKED ME.

1004
01:05:51,564 --> 01:05:54,567
WELL, SHE'S
A GOOD PERSON TO KNOW.

1005
01:05:54,567 --> 01:05:57,069
SO,

1006
01:05:57,069 --> 01:05:59,571
WHERE DID YOU
STUDY AGAIN ?

1007
01:05:59,572 --> 01:06:02,074
CARLTON.
OH.

1008
01:06:02,074 --> 01:06:04,576
CARLTON SCHOOL OF NURSING.

1009
01:06:06,579 --> 01:06:09,582
BUT I ONLY WENT
FOR TWO SEMESTERS THOUGH. OH.

1010
01:06:09,582 --> 01:06:13,085
'CAUSE DEL--
AH, RIGHT. OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

1011
01:06:13,085 --> 01:06:15,587
I THINK YOU SET
THE OFFICIAL RECORD...

1012
01:06:15,588 --> 01:06:18,591
FOR STAYING IN CHARACTER
ABOUT THREE HOURS AGO NOW.

1013
01:06:18,591 --> 01:06:23,095
[ Laughs ]
YOU JUST SAID THAT TO ME TWO HOURS AGO.

1014
01:06:26,098 --> 01:06:28,100
OHH--

1015
01:06:28,601 --> 01:06:30,603
IS IT HERE ?
MM-HMM.

1016
01:06:30,603 --> 01:06:33,105
WELL, GREAT.

1017
01:06:33,105 --> 01:06:37,859
GOSH.  I HAVEN'T BEEN
THIS HAPPY SINCE I WAS 12.

1018
01:06:39,862 --> 01:06:43,365
OKAY, I'LL BITE.
WHAT HAPPENED WHEN YOU WERE 12 ?

1019
01:06:43,366 --> 01:06:46,369
I TOOK MY MOM TO KANSAS CITY
FOR MOTHER'S DAY,

1020
01:06:46,369 --> 01:06:49,872
AND I USED THE ALLOWANCE
I WAS SAVING.

1021
01:06:49,872 --> 01:06:51,874
WE WENT TO LUNCH AT SKIES--

1022
01:06:51,874 --> 01:06:54,376
THIS RESTAURANT
AT THE TOP OF A BUILDING,

1023
01:06:54,377 --> 01:06:58,881
AND YOU CAN SEE THE WHOLE WORLD
FROM UP THERE.

1024
01:06:58,881 --> 01:07:01,383
IT WAS
OUR LAST SPECIAL THING...

1025
01:07:01,884 --> 01:07:04,386
'CAUSE SHE DIED THAT YEAR.

1026
01:07:06,889 --> 01:07:09,892
IT WAS A GREAT DAY.

1027
01:07:13,896 --> 01:07:17,399
YOU JUST... GAVE ME
GOOSE BUMPS FROM THAT, YOU KNOW THAT ?

1028
01:07:18,901 --> 01:07:21,403
THAT IS
JUST GREAT IMPROV.

1029
01:07:21,404 --> 01:07:24,407
I JUST WANT EVERYTHING
TO BE PERFECT BETWEEN US.

1030
01:07:24,407 --> 01:07:29,412
I KNOW, I KNOW.
LISTEN, LET'S, LET'S-- TIME, HERE.  LET'S--

1031
01:07:29,412 --> 01:07:33,416
CAN WE TALK SERIOUSLY
FOR... JUST A MINUTE ?

1032
01:07:33,916 --> 01:07:37,419
- UH-HUH.
- I KNOW HOW MUCH YOU WANT THIS, BETTY,

1033
01:07:37,420 --> 01:07:42,425
AND YOU ARE GIFTED
AND EXTREMELY DETERMINED,

1034
01:07:42,425 --> 01:07:45,928
BUT I GOTTA TELL YOU,
IT IS NOT ENTIRELY UP TO ME.

1035
01:07:45,928 --> 01:07:48,931
I KNOW.  IT'S UP TO US.

1036
01:08:01,944 --> 01:08:04,947
I LOVE YOU, DAVID,

1037
01:08:05,448 --> 01:08:08,951
AND I WANT TO SEE YOU
TOMORROW AND THE NEXT DAY...

1038
01:08:09,452 --> 01:08:11,954
AND THE NEXT DAY
AND THE NEXT.

1039
01:08:26,469 --> 01:08:28,971
<i>SO WERE YOU WITH HIM</i>
<i>THIS WHOLE TIME ?</i>

1040
01:08:28,971 --> 01:08:32,474
OH, YOU SCARED ME.
MM-HMM.

1041
01:08:32,475 --> 01:08:35,978
- STILL IN LOVE ?
- MM-HMM.

1042
01:08:36,479 --> 01:08:39,482
THIS ISN'T FAIR,
YOU KNOW.

1043
01:08:39,482 --> 01:08:41,484
DO YOU ALWAYS GET
WHAT YOU WANT ?

1044
01:08:41,484 --> 01:08:45,738
- ALMOST NEVER.
- BUT YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH SOMEONE WHO DOESN'T EXIST.

1045
01:08:46,238 --> 01:08:49,741
YOU COME OUT HERE,
YOU MEET THIS GUY WHO SHOULD LAUGH IN YOUR FACE.

1046
01:08:49,742 --> 01:08:52,244
INSTEAD,
YOU LEAVE WITH HIM.

1047
01:08:52,244 --> 01:08:55,747
YOU'RE, LIKE,
ONE OF A KIND.

1048
01:08:57,249 --> 01:08:58,917
THANKS.

1049
01:08:59,418 --> 01:09:02,421
[ George ]
IT WAS A TOTALLY REJUVENATING, SPIRITUAL EXPERIENCE.

1050
01:09:02,421 --> 01:09:04,423
I KNOW.  I WAS THERE.

1051
01:09:04,423 --> 01:09:07,426
I'M NOT DENYING
THAT SHE'S GOOD. THANK YOU, LUPITA.

1052
01:09:07,927 --> 01:09:10,429
YOU KNOW SHE GOT A JOB
AS A NURSE ?

1053
01:09:10,429 --> 01:09:12,431
METHOD ACTRESS ?

1054
01:09:12,431 --> 01:09:16,935
DAVID RAVELL--
HE'S GETTING BORING.

1055
01:09:16,936 --> 01:09:21,690
- WE KNOW THAT.
- <i>WELL, COULDN'T I HAVE,</i> <i>LIKE, A SISTER...</i>

1056
01:09:21,690 --> 01:09:24,693
WHO'S A TWIN WHO'S EVIL ?

1057
01:09:24,944 --> 01:09:28,948
NO !  WE DID THAT
WITH LONNIE.  REMEMBER THE BLIND ONE LAST YEAR ?

1058
01:09:28,948 --> 01:09:31,951
- HE GOT THE EMMY THING
FOR THAT ? - YEAH.

1059
01:09:33,452 --> 01:09:35,587
I THINK WE JUST
BRING BETTY DOWN...

1060
01:09:35,588 --> 01:09:38,457
AND JUST THROW HER
INTO THE SET AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

1061
01:09:38,457 --> 01:09:41,092
[ Laughing ]

1062
01:09:41,093 --> 01:09:43,211
- I DON'T KNOW.
- I MEAN, I TELL THE CAST AHEAD OF TIME.

1063
01:09:43,212 --> 01:09:46,348
- I MEAN, THEY'D ALL BE PREPPED.
- I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

1064
01:09:46,348 --> 01:09:50,352
IT'D BE LIKE LIVE TELEVISION.
I MEAN, LET'S LIVE ON THE EDGE A LITTLE BIT HERE.

1065
01:09:50,853 --> 01:09:53,472
COME ON, LYLA !
WE COULD BREAK THE MOULD.

1066
01:09:53,472 --> 01:09:55,974
I SAID
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

1067
01:10:18,464 --> 01:10:21,467
[ Charlie ]
NOW, LET ME TELL YOU WHY I KNOW SHE'S LYING.

1068
01:10:21,967 --> 01:10:26,471
FIRST PLACE,
BETTY WOULD NEVER FALL FOR A SOAP STAR.

1069
01:10:26,472 --> 01:10:28,474
<i>IT'S BENEATH HER.</i>

1070
01:10:28,474 --> 01:10:31,477
I DON'T KNOW.
THAT BARTENDER SOUNDED VERY SERIOUS. <i>NO, NO.</i>

1071
01:10:31,727 --> 01:10:34,229
BETTY'S HERE ON BUSINESS.

1072
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:37,233
IT'S THE BIGGEST MARKET
FOR WHAT SHE'S SELLING.

1073
01:10:37,233 --> 01:10:39,351
WAIT, HOLD UP, HOLD UP.
THAT DON'T MAKE NO SENSE.

1074
01:10:39,351 --> 01:10:41,853
WHAT DOESN'T MAKE NO SENSE ?
WELL, YOU OBVIOUSLY BELIEVE THE LADY.

1075
01:10:41,854 --> 01:10:43,856
SHIT, WE'RE ALL THE WAY
HERE IN L.A.

1076
01:10:43,856 --> 01:10:46,859
SO YOU BELIEVED HER ENOUGH
TO COME THE FUCK OUT HERE.

1077
01:10:46,859 --> 01:10:50,362
IF YOU BELIEVED HER THAT MUCH,
NOW WHY IS THE REST OF HER STORY SUDDENLY BULLSHIT ?

1078
01:10:50,863 --> 01:10:53,365
- I JUST DON'T BUY IT.
- DON'T BUY IT.

1079
01:10:53,499 --> 01:10:56,001
CALL IT INSTINCTS.
CALL IT 35 YEARS OF PROFESSIONAL KNOW-HOW.

1080
01:10:56,001 --> 01:10:59,004
I CALL IT NUTTY AS MY SHIT
AFTER I EAT AN ALMOND ROCA.

1081
01:10:59,004 --> 01:11:02,374
YOU NEED TO REMEMBER
WHO YOU'RE TALKING TO.

1082
01:11:02,374 --> 01:11:05,377
I NEED TO GET
MY FUCKIN' HEAD EXAMINED !

1083
01:11:05,377 --> 01:11:09,514
YOU CAN'T RULE SOMETHING OUT
JUST 'CAUSE YOU GOT A WHIM OR THOUGHT THE BITCH WAS FINE !

1084
01:11:09,515 --> 01:11:11,517
I'VE BEEN FOLLOWING YOUR WHIMS
ALL ACROSS AMERICA.

1085
01:11:12,017 --> 01:11:14,886
AND YOU KNOW WHAT ?
I AM FUCKIN' TIRED ! WESLEY--

1086
01:11:14,887 --> 01:11:18,390
IT'S BENEATH HER ?
THE BITCH IS A FUCKIN' HOUSEWIFE !

1087
01:11:18,390 --> 01:11:21,276
AIN'T NOTHIN' BENEATH HER !

1088
01:11:24,146 --> 01:11:26,648
SO CHECK THIS OUT.
WHAT KIND OF CAR DOES JASMINE DRIVE ?

1089
01:11:26,649 --> 01:11:29,401
UH, MERCEDES, I THINK.
BLACK.

1090
01:11:29,401 --> 01:11:31,903
SO IS SHE AS FINE IN REAL LIFE
AS SHE IS ON THE SHOW ?

1091
01:11:31,904 --> 01:11:35,157
- BETTER.
- MMM !  GODDAMN.

1092
01:11:35,157 --> 01:11:38,160
WHY DON'T YOU
HELP A BROTHER SNEAK ON THE LOT ?

1093
01:11:39,662 --> 01:11:42,297
SURE.

1094
01:11:42,798 --> 01:11:46,802
GOOD LOOKIN' OUT, BABY.
GOOD LOOKIN' OUT. ALL RIGHT, NOW.

1095
01:11:46,802 --> 01:11:51,056
BLACK MERCEDES.
LOOKIN' FOR A BLACK MERCEDES.

1096
01:11:52,558 --> 01:11:54,560
IT'S GOT TEN KILOS.

1097
01:11:54,560 --> 01:11:57,563
BLONDE, GREAT FIGURE.

1098
01:11:57,563 --> 01:12:02,067
SORT OF A WHOLESOME
DORIS DAY THING GOING.

1099
01:12:02,067 --> 01:12:06,571
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I SAID.
DORIS DAY.

1100
01:12:06,572 --> 01:12:11,577
YEAH, YOU COULD SEE HER
WORKIN' AT THE U.N. OR SOME PLACE LIKE THAT.

1101
01:12:11,577 --> 01:12:15,080
U.N.

1102
01:12:15,080 --> 01:12:18,083
UNITED NATIONS, MAN.
WHERE--  NEVER MIND.

1103
01:12:23,589 --> 01:12:26,592
[ Beeping ]

1104
01:12:26,592 --> 01:12:28,844
[ Doorbell Rings ]

1105
01:12:29,461 --> 01:12:32,464
HI.  BETTY THERE ?

1106
01:12:32,464 --> 01:12:34,966
YOU DON'T LOOK
LIKE YOU DO ON TV.

1107
01:12:39,722 --> 01:12:43,726
YOU MUST BE ROSA.
I'M GEORGE McCORD.

1108
01:12:51,734 --> 01:12:55,237
I'VE HEARD
SO MANY GREAT THINGS ABOUT YOU.

1109
01:12:55,237 --> 01:12:58,490
HMM.  NOT AS MUCH AS
I'VE HEARD ABOUT YOU.

1110
01:12:58,490 --> 01:13:00,492
THESE ARE FOR YOU.

1111
01:13:01,994 --> 01:13:03,996
[ Sniffs ]

1112
01:13:03,996 --> 01:13:08,000
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

1113
01:13:09,501 --> 01:13:12,003
HI.

1114
01:13:12,004 --> 01:13:14,506
OH, THAT'S NICE.

1115
01:13:14,506 --> 01:13:16,508
WELL, I SEE
YOU'VE MET DAVID.

1116
01:13:16,508 --> 01:13:19,511
YEAH, I SURE DID.
FUNNY THING, BETTY.

1117
01:13:19,511 --> 01:13:22,013
HE INTRODUCED HIMSELF
TO ME AS GEORGE.

1118
01:13:22,014 --> 01:13:25,017
OH, YEAH.
HE DOES THAT.

1119
01:13:25,017 --> 01:13:28,520
HALF THE PEOPLE WHO KNOW HIM
CALL HIM GEORGE.

1120
01:13:34,159 --> 01:13:36,661
I DON'T THINK
YOUR FRIEND ROSA LIKES ME VERY MUCH.

1121
01:13:36,662 --> 01:13:40,165
OH, SHE'S PROBABLY
JUST JEALOUS.

1122
01:13:40,165 --> 01:13:43,168
SHE GETS
A LITTLE CONFUSED ABOUT MEN.

1123
01:13:43,168 --> 01:13:45,170
UM, SO WHERE
ARE WE GOING ?

1124
01:13:45,671 --> 01:13:48,674
WELL, FIRST I WAS THINKING
ABOUT PATINA, AND THEN I THOUGHT ABOUT THE IVY,

1125
01:13:48,674 --> 01:13:52,177
AND THEN
I THOUGHT SOME PLACE A LITTLE MORE ROMANTIC,

1126
01:13:52,177 --> 01:13:55,180
LIKE MY PLACE.
OH, GREAT !

1127
01:13:55,180 --> 01:13:57,182
WE'RE GOING
TO THE BEACH HOUSE.

1128
01:13:57,182 --> 01:14:00,685
NO.  I DON'T LIVE
AT THE BEACH.  DAVID--

1129
01:14:00,686 --> 01:14:03,188
NO, I MOVED TO THE HILLS.

1130
01:14:03,188 --> 01:14:05,190
[ Laughs ]
I MOVED.

1131
01:14:06,191 --> 01:14:08,193
[ George ]
GOD, I HAVEN'T FELT LIKE THIS...

1132
01:14:08,694 --> 01:14:11,196
SINCE I WAS
WITH STELLA ADLER IN NEW YORK.

1133
01:14:11,196 --> 01:14:15,200
YOU JUST--  YOU'RE--
YOU'RE SO REAL.

1134
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:20,705
I DON'T THINK YOU'VE EVER
MENTIONED THIS STELLA TO ME BEFORE.

1135
01:14:20,706 --> 01:14:23,208
OH, HAVEN'T I ?
MM-MM.

1136
01:14:23,208 --> 01:14:26,211
SEE, I WOULD REMEMBER
THE NAME STELLA.

1137
01:14:26,211 --> 01:14:30,715
THE ONLY STELLA I EVER KNEW
WAS A PARROT.

1138
01:14:30,716 --> 01:14:35,837
SO WAS THAT BEFORE LESLIE ?
BEFORE US ?

1139
01:14:35,838 --> 01:14:38,340
I'VE NEVER MET
ANYONE LIKE YOU, BETTY.

1140
01:14:38,340 --> 01:14:43,345
WELL, THAT'S WHY WE'RE
MEANT TO BE TOGETHER.

1141
01:14:45,347 --> 01:14:47,849
YOUR DEDICATION
SCARES ME.

1142
01:14:48,350 --> 01:14:52,854
OH, IT'S EASY TO BE DEDICATED
WHEN YOU CARE ABOUT SOMETHING.

1143
01:14:54,356 --> 01:14:57,359
WHEN I MET YOU,
IT WAS LIKE A WARM BREEZE...

1144
01:14:57,359 --> 01:15:01,363
THAT'S SUDDENLY
BLOWN INTO MY LIFE.

1145
01:15:01,363 --> 01:15:05,367
YOU REMEMBER THAT LINE ?
I SAID THAT TO LESLIE DURING HER FUNERAL.

1146
01:15:05,367 --> 01:15:07,369
I LOVE THAT LINE.

1147
01:15:07,369 --> 01:15:10,372
WELL,

1148
01:15:10,372 --> 01:15:14,376
YOU SAID IT TO HER,

1149
01:15:14,376 --> 01:15:18,380
BUT YOU MEANT IT FOR ME,
DIDN'T YOU ?

1150
01:15:22,885 --> 01:15:25,387
YEAH.

1151
01:15:25,888 --> 01:15:27,890
MAYBE I DID.

1152
01:15:54,833 --> 01:15:57,335
[ Wesley ]
SO I'M WALKIN' DOWN HOLLYWOOD BOULEVARD,

1153
01:15:57,336 --> 01:15:59,471
CHECKING OUT
ALL THE STARS ON THE GROUND.

1154
01:15:59,471 --> 01:16:01,473
CLINT EASTWOOD,
ROCK HUDSON. NO PEOPLE OF RACE.

1155
01:16:01,473 --> 01:16:03,975
NOT ONE--
I COULD NOT FIND PEOPLE OF RACE ANYWHERE, RIGHT ?

1156
01:16:03,976 --> 01:16:05,978
SO I'M LOOKING
AT THIS CHINESE GUY.

1157
01:16:05,978 --> 01:16:08,847
HE'S READING HIS PAPER,
AND I LOOK REAL HARD, AND WHO DO I SEE ?

1158
01:16:09,097 --> 01:16:11,099
THAT'S LONNIE,
THE MAIN PRICK FROM THE SHOW.

1159
01:16:11,099 --> 01:16:13,601
AND WHO IS THAT
NEXT TO HIM ?  BETTY ! THAT'S DEFINITELY BETTY.

1160
01:16:13,602 --> 01:16:16,605
I TOLD YOU THIS
AIN'T NO COINCIDENCE.

1161
01:16:21,610 --> 01:16:23,612
WHAT THE FUCK ?
YOU BEEN HOLDING OUT ON ME ?

1162
01:16:24,112 --> 01:16:26,614
- THIS DOES NOT FIT
HER PROFILE. - FUCK THE PROFILE !

1163
01:16:26,615 --> 01:16:29,618
THAT'S THE SAME GUY !
NO, NO.  NO, NO.

1164
01:16:29,618 --> 01:16:33,622
BETTY WOULD NOT BE HERE
BECAUSE OF A SOAP OPERA. NOT A SOAP OPERA, MAN !

1165
01:16:33,622 --> 01:16:36,124
THAT WOULD MAKE HER--
THAT WOULD MAKE HER CRAZY !

1166
01:16:36,124 --> 01:16:39,127
NO SHIT, SHAFT !
AND YOU AIN'T TOO FAR BEHIND YOURSELF.

1167
01:16:39,127 --> 01:16:41,129
NO, NO.
BETTY'S SMARTER THAN THAT.

1168
01:16:41,129 --> 01:16:43,631
HOW THE FUCK DID YOU
STAY ON THIS JOB SO FUCKIN' LONG ?

1169
01:16:44,132 --> 01:16:46,134
WE ARE DRAGGIN' OUR ASS
UP AND DOWN THE COUNTRY.

1170
01:16:46,134 --> 01:16:50,138
MEANWHILE, OUR ANSWER
TO OUR PRAYERS ARE RIGHT IN YOUR BACK FUCKIN' POCKET.

1171
01:16:50,138 --> 01:16:53,141
YOU LET THIS CUNT
FUCK UP MY--

1172
01:16:53,141 --> 01:16:55,643
DON'T YOU TALK TO BETTY
THAT WAY.

1173
01:16:55,644 --> 01:16:57,646
I DON'T CARE
WHAT SHE TURNS OUT TO BE.

1174
01:16:57,646 --> 01:17:00,148
DON'T YOU USE THAT TERM AGAIN.
YOU HEAR ME ?

1175
01:17:00,148 --> 01:17:03,651
YOU NEED THERAPY.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ?

1176
01:17:03,652 --> 01:17:08,657
YES, I UNDERSTAND !
NOW LET GO OF MY VEST. YOU'RE STRETCHING IT.

1177
01:17:14,663 --> 01:17:17,165
YOU MADE YOUR POINT.

1178
01:17:26,558 --> 01:17:29,060
GET YOURSELF READY.
GET READY ?

1179
01:17:29,061 --> 01:17:33,065
SHIT, I'VE BEEN READY
SINCE OKLAHOMA. "GET READY."

1180
01:17:34,066 --> 01:17:36,568
READY FOR WHAT ?

1181
01:17:47,579 --> 01:17:49,447
[ Giggles ]
NO PEEKING, ALL RIGHT ?

1182
01:17:49,948 --> 01:17:52,450
HOW MUCH LONGER ?
NOT MUCH.

1183
01:17:52,451 --> 01:17:54,453
HERE WE GO.
THERE'S NOTHING IN FRONT OF YOU.

1184
01:17:54,953 --> 01:17:57,455
RELAX.  YOU GOT
A LITTLE STEP THERE. [ Laughing ]

1185
01:17:57,456 --> 01:17:59,458
YOU'RE FINE, YOU'RE FINE.

1186
01:17:59,458 --> 01:18:01,960
ALL RIGHT.  ALL SET ?
UH-HUH.

1187
01:18:01,960 --> 01:18:04,462
HERE WE GO.  AND--

1188
01:18:05,464 --> 01:18:07,466
SURPRISE.
[ Gasps ]

1189
01:18:07,849 --> 01:18:09,851
LOMA VISTA.

1190
01:18:09,851 --> 01:18:14,355
<i>- TA-DA !</i>
<i>- YOU DIDN'T TELL ME I WAS</i> <i>GONNA MEET YOUR FRIENDS.</i>

1191
01:18:14,356 --> 01:18:17,359
GUESS WHAT.
YOU GOT THE JOB.

1192
01:18:17,359 --> 01:18:20,362
AND I'M DIRECTING.
OH, BUT I'M AT L.A. COUNTY.

1193
01:18:20,362 --> 01:18:22,364
OH, ARE YOU ?
COME ON.

1194
01:18:22,364 --> 01:18:24,866
IT'S ONLY FOUR LINES,
SO I JUST THOUGHT I'D KIND OF SPRING IT ON YOU.

1195
01:18:24,866 --> 01:18:28,369
HOPE THAT'S OKAY.
WE'RE NOT GONNA DO ANY BLOCKING OR ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

1196
01:18:28,370 --> 01:18:30,372
I'M JUST GONNA PUT YOU HERE
NEAR THE NURSE'S STATION--

1197
01:18:30,372 --> 01:18:32,374
OKAY, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.
OKAY ?  THANKS.

1198
01:18:32,374 --> 01:18:34,876
AND I JUST WANNA DO
LIKE A QUICK RUN-THROUGH, ALL RIGHT ?

1199
01:18:34,876 --> 01:18:39,380
RELAX.  YOU LOOK GREAT.
AND HERE WE GO IN A SEC. HOLD ON.

1200
01:18:44,503 --> 01:18:46,505
TRAFFIC WAS A NIGHTMARE
COMING OVER THE HILL.

1201
01:18:46,505 --> 01:18:50,509
THAT'S FINE.
WE'VE ONLY GOT... 70 PAGES TO SHOOT TODAY.

1202
01:18:50,509 --> 01:18:52,511
TAKE YOUR TIME.

1203
01:18:53,011 --> 01:18:55,513
DAVID !

1204
01:18:55,514 --> 01:18:58,517
WE'LL GET YOU IN YOUR HAIR
AND MAKE-UP AFTER THIS. JUST PUT THIS ON.

1205
01:18:58,517 --> 01:19:00,519
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ?

1206
01:19:00,519 --> 01:19:03,021
UM--

1207
01:19:03,021 --> 01:19:07,025
HI.  WELCOME.
I HEAR YOU'RE REALLY GOOD.

1208
01:19:07,025 --> 01:19:10,028
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE ? GOOD LUCK.

1209
01:19:10,028 --> 01:19:12,030
<i>DAVID !</i>

1210
01:19:12,030 --> 01:19:15,033
YOUR LINES ARE ON
THE CUE CARDS OVER HERE. WHAT IS SHE DOING HERE ?

1211
01:19:15,033 --> 01:19:17,535
OH.  BUT FEEL FREE
TO AD-LIB, OKAY ?

1212
01:19:17,536 --> 01:19:19,538
AD-LIB ?
IN FACT, I WANT YOU TO AD-LIB.

1213
01:19:19,538 --> 01:19:22,541
I KNOW.  I HATE THESE.
BUT THAT'S THE MAGIC THAT I'M AFTER.

1214
01:19:22,541 --> 01:19:24,543
YOU KNOW, JUST TO LET IT GO,
HAVE FUN WITH IT.

1215
01:19:24,543 --> 01:19:27,045
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
A WHOLE NEW FEEL TO THE SHOW.  ERIC !

1216
01:19:27,045 --> 01:19:29,047
YOU KNOW ?  SO JUST
DO ONE OF THOSE-- JUST--  [ Exhales ]

1217
01:19:29,047 --> 01:19:32,550
YOU KNOW, LET IT OUT
AND JUST HAVE FUN WITH IT. YOU REMEMBER BETTY ?

1218
01:19:32,551 --> 01:19:35,053
YES.
LET'S GO.

1219
01:19:35,053 --> 01:19:39,057
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>SETTLE, PLEASE.</i> <i>STAND BY.  REHEARSAL.</i>

1220
01:19:39,307 --> 01:19:41,442
BETTY ?

1221
01:19:41,693 --> 01:19:43,695
JUST DO WHAT
YOU'VE BEEN DOING, OKAY ?

1222
01:19:43,695 --> 01:19:46,064
WATCH THE SCENE,
TAKE YOUR CUE FROM HERE.

1223
01:19:46,064 --> 01:19:49,067
HANK.
LINES ARE OVER HERE.

1224
01:19:49,067 --> 01:19:51,069
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>HERE WE GO.  IN...</i>

1225
01:19:51,570 --> 01:19:57,208
<i>FIVE, FOUR,</i>
<i>THREE, TWO--</i>

1226
01:19:57,209 --> 01:20:01,213
IS THIS SOME KIND OF A GAME ?
NO, IT'S MORE LIKE A NIGHTMARE I CAN'T WAKE UP FROM.

1227
01:20:01,213 --> 01:20:05,217
THERE ARE OTHER PEOPLE
IN THIS NIGHTMARE, AND THEY'RE GOING TO GET HURT.

1228
01:20:05,333 --> 01:20:09,337
<i>- UH, I FEEL SO--</i>
<i>ARM, PLEASE.</i> <i>- OH.</i>

1229
01:20:09,337 --> 01:20:11,339
I FEEL SO ALONE
RIGHT NOW.

1230
01:20:11,840 --> 01:20:14,342
HERE WE GO.
SHOW TIME.  SHOW TIME.

1231
01:20:30,108 --> 01:20:33,111
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT ?
I THINK YOU STEPPED ON MY FIRST LINE--

1232
01:20:33,111 --> 01:20:35,613
I WAS TALKING TO HER.
DO YOU NEED ANYTHING ?

1233
01:20:42,621 --> 01:20:45,624
LISTEN, I'M SORRY.
I THOUGHT THIS WOULD BE THE BEST WAY,

1234
01:20:45,624 --> 01:20:47,626
JUST KIND OF
THROW YOU INTO IT, YOU KNOW ?

1235
01:20:47,626 --> 01:20:50,629
[ Lyla ]
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON ? IF YOU NEED LIKE A MINUTE...

1236
01:20:50,629 --> 01:20:53,131
JUST TO GET YOUR INSTRUMENTS
STRAIGHT, THAT'S FINE. CAN I TALK TO YOU ?

1237
01:20:53,131 --> 01:20:57,635
IF YOU WANNA JUST--
CAN I TALK TO YOU ? JUST A SECOND.

1238
01:21:02,641 --> 01:21:05,644
DAVID.
STOP CALLING ME DAVID, FOR CHRIST'S SAKE.

1239
01:21:05,644 --> 01:21:07,646
WE'RE ON THE SET.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO CALL ME DAVID HERE, OKAY ?

1240
01:21:07,646 --> 01:21:11,650
WHAT'S GOING ON ?
WHAT IS GOING ON WHAT ?

1241
01:21:11,650 --> 01:21:14,152
YOU'RE ACTING CRAZY HERE.

1242
01:21:14,152 --> 01:21:17,655
ISN'T THIS EXACTLY
WHAT YOU WANTED ? I DON'T KNOW.

1243
01:21:17,656 --> 01:21:20,158
IS THERE A PROBLEM,
GEORGE ? <i>NO, NO, NO.</i>

1244
01:21:20,158 --> 01:21:22,160
NO PROBLEM.  THERE'S--

1245
01:21:22,160 --> 01:21:25,913
WHAT IS THE PROBLEM ?
JUST DO THAT THING THAT YOU DO.

1246
01:21:25,914 --> 01:21:29,918
I MEAN, COME ON !
YOU DROVE ME NUTS WITH THIS FOR THREE DAYS.

1247
01:21:29,918 --> 01:21:32,420
NOW, JUST RELAX AND,
AND LET'S DO IT.

1248
01:21:32,420 --> 01:21:36,424
HERE WE GO.  HERE WE GO.
YOU'RE FINE.  YOU'LL BE FINE. HERE WE GO.  SORRY ABOUT THAT.

1249
01:21:36,424 --> 01:21:38,926
ALL RIGHT ?
HERE WE GO.

1250
01:21:38,927 --> 01:21:43,932
- <i>FIVE, FOUR, THREE, TWO--</i>
<i>-</i> <i>IS THIS SOME KIND OF GAME</i> <i>THAT YOU'RE PLAYING ?</i>

1251
01:21:44,432 --> 01:21:46,434
NO.  IT'S MORE LIKE
A NIGHTMARE I CAN'T WAKE UP FROM.

1252
01:21:46,434 --> 01:21:51,822
THERE ARE OTHER PEOPLE
IN THAT NIGHTMARE, AND THEY'RE GOING TO GET HURT.

1253
01:21:52,324 --> 01:21:54,826
OH, NO.  OH, NO.
OH, NO.

1254
01:21:54,826 --> 01:21:56,828
BETTY ?

1255
01:21:56,828 --> 01:21:59,080
[ George ]
OH, NO.

1256
01:21:59,080 --> 01:22:04,952
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

1257
01:22:05,453 --> 01:22:09,089
<i>THIS IS BULLSHIT !</i>
<i>I CANNOT WORK LIKE THIS !</i>

1258
01:22:09,090 --> 01:22:11,592
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY,
TAKE FIVE. NO.  HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

1259
01:22:11,593 --> 01:22:14,095
LET ME JUST TALK TO HER.
IT WAS A GAMBLE. IT DIDN'T WORK.

1260
01:22:14,346 --> 01:22:17,465
- <i>WE HAVE TO MOVE ON.</i>
<i>- GODDAMN IT !  SHE'S BEEN</i> <i>DOING THIS ALL WEEK !</i>

1261
01:22:17,465 --> 01:22:19,467
SHE CAN DO IT NOW !
I SAID FORGET IT !

1262
01:22:19,467 --> 01:22:22,970
ALL RIGHT.  WELL--
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT, ERIC ?

1263
01:22:22,971 --> 01:22:27,475
I HOPE YOU'RE HAPPY.
I JUST PUT MY ASS ON THE LINE FOR YOU,

1264
01:22:27,475 --> 01:22:29,977
AND MY REPUTATION,
AND YOU JUST MADE A TOTAL IDIOT OUT OF ME.

1265
01:22:30,478 --> 01:22:32,480
YOU HAPPY ?
I'M SORRY. WHAT DID I DO ?

1266
01:22:32,480 --> 01:22:34,982
WHO PUT YOU UP TO THIS ?
DID MY EX-WIFE DO THIS ?

1267
01:22:34,983 --> 01:22:36,985
- YOU KNOW, DAVID--
- STOP CALLING ME THAT !

1268
01:22:37,485 --> 01:22:39,987
MY NAME IS GEORGE !
GEORGE !  SAY IT !

1269
01:22:39,988 --> 01:22:42,490
THIS IS A TV SHOW !
A TELEVISION SHOW !

1270
01:22:42,490 --> 01:22:44,742
IF YOU DON'T KNOW THE
DIFFERENCE, YOU'RE MORE FUCKED UP THAN I THOUGHT !

1271
01:22:44,743 --> 01:22:48,379
- LEAVE HER ALONE, GEORGE.
- <i>SHUT THE FUCK UP !</i> <i>YOU'RE A GRIP.  GO...</i>

1272
01:22:48,380 --> 01:22:50,382
GRIP SOMETHING !

1273
01:22:50,882 --> 01:22:52,884
AND YOU ARE NOT
AN ACTRESS, ARE YOU ? YOU'RE--  WHAT ARE YOU ?

1274
01:22:52,884 --> 01:22:55,386
YOU'RE LIKE
A SOAP OPERA GROUPIE, RIGHT ?

1275
01:22:55,387 --> 01:22:58,890
IS THAT IT ?
YOU HAVE NOTHING BETTER TO DO BUT THIS !

1276
01:22:58,890 --> 01:23:01,893
WHY DON'T YOU
GET A FUCKING LIFE AND STOP RUINING MINE !

1277
01:23:01,893 --> 01:23:03,895
OH, BOY.
SHE GAVE ME THIS ONE SHOT--

1278
01:23:03,895 --> 01:23:07,398
ONE SHOT IN MY LIFE TO DO THIS,
AND YOU HAVE DESTROYED IT.

1279
01:23:07,399 --> 01:23:09,901
THANK YOU VERY MUCH !
THANKS, BETTY ! THAT WAS GREAT !

1280
01:23:09,901 --> 01:23:13,905
[ Voices Fade Out ]

1281
01:23:16,408 --> 01:23:19,411
[ No Audio ]

1282
01:23:19,411 --> 01:23:23,915
ARE YOU HEARING THIS ?
HEY !

1283
01:23:24,416 --> 01:23:28,420
SHE'S FUCKIN' CRAZY !
DON'T LOOK AT ME LIKE THAT ! YOU--  TELL 'EM WHO I--  HEY !

1284
01:23:28,420 --> 01:23:31,423
TELL 'EM WHO I AM.
TELL 'EM.

1285
01:23:31,539 --> 01:23:33,541
GEORGE McCORD ?

1286
01:23:33,541 --> 01:23:36,043
NO, NO, NO.
NO, NOT NOW.

1287
01:23:36,044 --> 01:23:37,545
I'M DAVID.
I AM DR. DAVID RAVELL.

1288
01:23:38,046 --> 01:23:40,048
<i>I'M THE GREAT</i>
<i>DR. DAVID RAVELL, RIGHT ?</i>

1289
01:23:40,048 --> 01:23:42,050
LOMA VISTA'S GREATEST--
I'M THE DOCTOR !

1290
01:23:42,550 --> 01:23:45,052
I DON'T THINK
THAT SHE THINKS THAT ! WHO DID YOU CALL ME ?

1291
01:23:45,303 --> 01:23:47,305
SHE CALLED YOU GEORGE,
GEORGE.

1292
01:23:47,689 --> 01:23:50,692
GEORGE McCORD,
MY-MY FAVORITE ACTOR ?

1293
01:23:50,692 --> 01:23:52,694
OH, OH.  OH, GOD.

1294
01:23:52,694 --> 01:23:57,198
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE ?
- OH, GOODNESS. OH, YOU'RE SICK.

1295
01:23:57,198 --> 01:23:59,700
UM--
WHAT DO YOU DO NOW ?

1296
01:23:59,701 --> 01:24:02,320
ARE YOU GONNA KILL ME ?
NO !  DON'T GET NEAR ME !

1297
01:24:02,821 --> 01:24:04,823
DON'T TOUCH ANYTHING,
CRAZY PERSON !

1298
01:24:04,823 --> 01:24:08,827
WHAT DO YOU DO NOW ?
WHAT ? HUH ?

1299
01:24:10,328 --> 01:24:12,830
UM--

1300
01:24:14,833 --> 01:24:17,836
I'M GONNA GO.

1301
01:24:19,337 --> 01:24:22,840
[ Man ]
OKAY.  MOVING ON. WARDROBE ?

1302
01:24:44,779 --> 01:24:46,781
HOW DO YOU DO,
MR. McCORD ?

1303
01:24:46,781 --> 01:24:50,785
WE'RE TRYING TO LOCATE
A DERANGED FAN OF YOURS, A MISS BETTY--

1304
01:24:50,785 --> 01:24:54,038
DERANGED.  YEAH.
THAT'D BE THE RIGHT WORD FOR IT.

1305
01:24:54,038 --> 01:24:58,042
THAT'S NOT NECESSARY.
UH, SHE'S STAYING WITH A FRIEND OF HERS,

1306
01:24:58,543 --> 01:25:03,047
ROSA... HERRERAS
OR HERNANDEZ OR--

1307
01:25:03,047 --> 01:25:06,050
HAS AN "H" SOUND TO IT.
THEY'RE IN SILVERLAKE.

1308
01:25:06,551 --> 01:25:09,554
THAT'S ALL I KNOW.
YEAH. SILVERLAKE.

1309
01:25:11,806 --> 01:25:15,192
YOU MUST GET THIS A LOT.
MM-HMM.

1310
01:25:15,193 --> 01:25:18,696
MORE THAN YOU KNOW.

1311
01:25:18,696 --> 01:25:20,698
ANYTHING ELSE ?

1312
01:25:21,199 --> 01:25:24,202
NO.
OKAY, GREAT. ACTUALLY, THERE IS.

1313
01:25:24,202 --> 01:25:27,572
YOU KNOW,
I'M A BIG FAN OF THE SHOW,

1314
01:25:27,572 --> 01:25:29,574
AND I FIGURE YOU BEING
DR. RAVELL AND ALL,

1315
01:25:29,574 --> 01:25:33,578
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE
ABLE TO GO OUT THERE AND TELL JASMINE TO COME OUTSIDE.

1316
01:25:33,962 --> 01:25:37,465
WELL, YOU THOUGHT WRONG.
HEY, MAN, IT'S JUST AN AUTOGRAPH.  IT'S NOT FOR ME.

1317
01:25:37,465 --> 01:25:39,467
IT NEVER IS.
MOTHERFUCKER !

1318
01:25:39,834 --> 01:25:41,836
YOU NEED TO HAVE
SOME FUCKIN' MANNERS, MAN !

1319
01:25:41,836 --> 01:25:44,839
WHAT THE FUCK IS
WRONG WITH YOU, MAN ? HEY, I SAW YOUR TV MOVIE !

1320
01:25:44,839 --> 01:25:49,226
IT SUCKED !
HASSELHOFF BLEW YOU OFF THE SCREEN !

1321
01:25:55,984 --> 01:25:59,487
BETTY ?

1322
01:25:59,487 --> 01:26:02,106
HEY, DID THE PIZZA GUY
SHOW UP YET ?

1323
01:26:07,612 --> 01:26:11,499
- CAN I HAVE THESE CHIPS ?
- SURE.

1324
01:26:11,866 --> 01:26:14,368
THANKS.

1325
01:26:14,369 --> 01:26:16,871
<i>ARE YOU ALL RIGHT ?</i>

1326
01:26:16,871 --> 01:26:19,256
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN ?

1327
01:26:37,942 --> 01:26:40,444
OH, SHIT !  WHAT THE--

1328
01:26:44,699 --> 01:26:47,702
CALL A DOCTOR, BITCH.
WHAT THE FUCK.

1329
01:26:47,702 --> 01:26:50,071
[ Dog Barking ]

1330
01:26:57,712 --> 01:27:00,214
[ Charlie ]
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT ? <i>DON'T ASK.</i>

1331
01:27:00,215 --> 01:27:04,219
IT'S ALL THERE.
HASN'T BEEN TOUCHED.

1332
01:27:05,720 --> 01:27:09,223
YOU WERE RIGHT ABOUT DEL.
HE WASN'T LYING.

1333
01:27:09,224 --> 01:27:14,345
YEAH, WELL,
YOU WERE RIGHT ABOUT WHAT THE LADY BARTENDER SAID.

1334
01:27:14,345 --> 01:27:16,347
YEAH, BUT YOU
WERE RIGHT FIRST.

1335
01:27:16,347 --> 01:27:19,983
YOU GOTTA FOLLOW
YOUR INSTINCTS.

1336
01:27:19,984 --> 01:27:22,486
SO WHAT DO YOUR INSTINCTS
TELL YOU NOW, KID ?

1337
01:27:22,604 --> 01:27:25,106
TAKE THIS SHIT
BACK TO DETROIT AND GET OUR FUCKIN' MONEY.

1338
01:27:25,356 --> 01:27:27,858
YEAH, WE COULD DO THAT.

1339
01:27:27,859 --> 01:27:29,861
I COULD BE
ON MY WAY TO FLORIDA.

1340
01:27:29,861 --> 01:27:33,865
YOU COULD GO ON DOWN
TO THAILAND OR SOME PLACE AND FUCK YOUR BRAINS OUT.

1341
01:27:33,998 --> 01:27:36,500
BUT THAT'S NOT WHAT
WE'RE GONNA DO, IS IT ? NO.

1342
01:27:37,001 --> 01:27:40,004
SHE'S MY LAST ONE.

1343
01:27:40,004 --> 01:27:44,008
MY INSTINCTS ARE TELLING ME
I'VE GOT TO SEE THIS THROUGH WITH HER.

1344
01:27:44,008 --> 01:27:46,510
AND IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I'VE TRIED TO TEACH YOU HERE--

1345
01:27:46,628 --> 01:27:51,015
- IT'S TO FOLLOW MY INSTINCTS.
- NO.  IT'S TO FOLLOW MY INSTINCTS.

1346
01:27:51,015 --> 01:27:53,517
SO WE GO UP THERE
AND WE CONCLUDE OUR BUSINESS.

1347
01:27:53,518 --> 01:27:55,520
CASE CLOSED.

1348
01:27:55,520 --> 01:27:57,772
I HAVE TO LEAVE.

1349
01:27:57,772 --> 01:28:00,775
LEAVE ?
WHERE YOU GOING ? MM-HMM.

1350
01:28:00,775 --> 01:28:02,777
KANSAS.
TONIGHT ?

1351
01:28:02,777 --> 01:28:04,779
UH-HUH.

1352
01:28:04,779 --> 01:28:07,782
YOU'RE GONNA DRIVE
HALFWAY ACROSS THE COUNTRY THIS MINUTE ?

1353
01:28:07,782 --> 01:28:11,285
UH-HUH.  I HAVE TO GO
FIX WHAT HAPPENED TO MY HUSBAND.

1354
01:28:11,286 --> 01:28:14,289
SO NOW YOU HAVE
A HUSBAND.

1355
01:28:14,289 --> 01:28:19,294
HAD.  HE WAS KILLED
IN THE DINING ROOM.

1356
01:28:19,294 --> 01:28:22,797
- HUH ?
- YOU KNOW, I THINK I SAW THE WHOLE THING.

1357
01:28:22,797 --> 01:28:25,800
I REMEMBER BLOOD EVERYWHERE
AND EVERYTHING.

1358
01:28:26,167 --> 01:28:30,671
SO WHAT ARE YOU SAYING,
BETTY, HUH ?  HUH ?

1359
01:28:30,672 --> 01:28:33,675
I REALLY DON'T KNOW.
<i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

1360
01:28:33,675 --> 01:28:39,180
YEAH, JUST A MINUTE !
THIS IS CRAZY, BETTY, OKAY ?  JUST DON'T GO.

1361
01:28:39,314 --> 01:28:41,316
JUST STAY HERE,
AND I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

1362
01:28:46,321 --> 01:28:50,074
- HOW MUCH ?
- UH, DETECTIVE JEFFERSON.

1363
01:28:50,074 --> 01:28:53,193
OH.  DID BETTY CALL YOU ?

1364
01:29:02,203 --> 01:29:06,707
SHE'S GOT PROBLEMS,
BUT... SHE'S NO KILLER.

1365
01:29:08,710 --> 01:29:12,213
I HOPE YOU GUYS
CAN JUST STRAIGHTEN THIS OUT.

1366
01:29:12,213 --> 01:29:15,216
GO EASY ON HER, OKAY,
'CAUSE SHE'S HAD A REALLY ROUGH DAY.

1367
01:29:15,216 --> 01:29:20,221
HEY, ROSA ?
THESE GUYS ARE HERE TO HELP YOU, BETTY.

1368
01:29:20,221 --> 01:29:23,857
- I DON'T THINK SO.
- COME ON !  COME HERE ! COME HERE !  COME ON !

1369
01:29:23,858 --> 01:29:26,610
<i>GET THE FUCK OVER THERE !</i>
<i>COME ON !</i>

1370
01:29:26,728 --> 01:29:28,730
SIT DOWN !  SHUT UP !

1371
01:29:30,231 --> 01:29:33,734
SO, WE MEET AGAIN.

1372
01:29:41,242 --> 01:29:45,379
I'VE SPENT MANY LONG HOURS
IN THE CAR WITH YOUR FACE STARING BACK AT ME.

1373
01:29:45,380 --> 01:29:50,001
- I'VE SEEN IT PAINTED
ON THE HORIZON. - WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU ?

1374
01:29:50,001 --> 01:29:51,502
HUH ?
<i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

1375
01:29:51,753 --> 01:29:55,006
THAT'S OUR PIZZA.
WESLEY--

1376
01:29:55,139 --> 01:29:57,641
COME HERE, COME HERE.
GET RID OF 'EM. YOU UNDERSTAND ?

1377
01:29:57,892 --> 01:29:59,894
OKAY.

1378
01:30:07,235 --> 01:30:09,353
HI.

1379
01:30:09,737 --> 01:30:12,239
BETTY, BOY,
AM I GLAD TO SEE YOU.

1380
01:30:12,240 --> 01:30:17,245
- ROY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE ?
- YOU ARE IN SERIOUS DANGER.

1381
01:30:17,361 --> 01:30:20,364
OH ?  WELL, ROY,
IT'S REALLY NOT A GOOD TIME RIGHT NOW.

1382
01:30:20,364 --> 01:30:23,867
BETTY, I WOULD'VE
BEEN HERE SOONER, BUT ELDEN PUT ME IN JAIL.

1383
01:30:23,868 --> 01:30:28,255
- <i>HE STILL THINKS THAT</i>
<i>YOU HAD DEL SCALPED.</i> <i>- HEY, I NEVER SAID THAT, OKAY ?</i>

1384
01:30:28,756 --> 01:30:32,009
HI, SHERIFF.
I DON'T THINK--

1385
01:30:32,009 --> 01:30:34,878
BETTY, LOOK, OPEN UP.
I GOTTA ASK YOU SOME QUESTIONS ABOUT--

1386
01:30:34,879 --> 01:30:37,381
BETTY, I REALLY THINK
IT'S IMPORTANT TO FIND OUT--

1387
01:30:37,765 --> 01:30:40,267
IT'S JUST REALLY,
REALLY NOT A GREAT TIME.

1388
01:30:40,635 --> 01:30:43,771
HEY.  HEY !

1389
01:30:43,771 --> 01:30:47,775
DON'T GIVE ME THAT !
I'VE COME 2,000 MILES FOR THIS !

1390
01:30:48,142 --> 01:30:51,645
AH !

1391
01:30:51,779 --> 01:30:55,282
YOU PROBABLY FLEW.
COME ON.

1392
01:30:57,285 --> 01:30:59,787
I CROSSED THE RIVER STYX
TO FIND HER, PAL.

1393
01:31:00,288 --> 01:31:04,041
I TRAVELLED
THE FUCKIN' COUNTRY TO GET HERE.

1394
01:31:04,041 --> 01:31:09,546
- WHO ARE THESE IDIOTS ?
- UH, THAT'S ROY OSTREY. HE'S A REPORTER.

1395
01:31:09,547 --> 01:31:15,052
AND THAT'S SHERIFF BALLARD.
HE, UH--  WELL, WE WENT TO FAIR OAKS HIGH.

1396
01:31:15,052 --> 01:31:17,921
OH, GREAT.  THIS IS--
THIS IS GREAT.

1397
01:31:17,922 --> 01:31:19,924
SIT YOUR ASS DOWN !

1398
01:31:19,924 --> 01:31:23,427
WHAT'S UP ?  WHAT'S UP ?
COME HERE.  COME HERE. COME HERE, MOTHERFUCK !

1399
01:31:23,427 --> 01:31:27,431
FUCK, MAN.
COME HERE.  COME HERE. YOU NEED AN INVITATION ?

1400
01:31:27,431 --> 01:31:29,566
I GOT TWO KIDS AND A DOG.
YEAH.  WHO DON'T ?

1401
01:31:31,819 --> 01:31:34,071
[ Groans ]
WHAT, WHAT, YOU GONNA SHOOT ME ?

1402
01:31:34,071 --> 01:31:36,573
WHAT YOU GONNA DO ?

1403
01:31:36,574 --> 01:31:39,076
<i>[ Handcuffs Ratcheting ]</i>

1404
01:31:40,077 --> 01:31:44,448
WHAT YOU DOIN' ?
ACT PROFESSIONAL !

1405
01:31:44,582 --> 01:31:49,587
- THAT'S NOT PROFESSIONAL !
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME. FIND OUT WHAT THEY KNOW.

1406
01:31:49,954 --> 01:31:51,956
SHIT.
[ Door Closes ]

1407
01:31:51,956 --> 01:31:54,291
OHH.

1408
01:31:54,292 --> 01:31:56,794
OH, OKAY.

1409
01:31:56,794 --> 01:31:59,296
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

1410
01:31:59,297 --> 01:32:04,302
OKAY !  UM, UM, UM--

1411
01:32:09,807 --> 01:32:15,445
<i>[ Whimpering ]</i>

1412
01:32:15,947 --> 01:32:19,951
I SUPPOSE...
YOU WANT ME, UM--

1413
01:32:19,951 --> 01:32:23,454
WHAT ?
[ Sobbing ]

1414
01:32:23,454 --> 01:32:26,457
TO TAKE OFF MY, UM--

1415
01:32:26,457 --> 01:32:28,959
OH, NO, NO.

1416
01:32:29,210 --> 01:32:32,463
- NO ?
- YOU KNOW WHO I AM ?

1417
01:32:32,463 --> 01:32:36,467
OH, I'VE GOT
A PRETTY GOOD IDEA. LISTEN.

1418
01:32:36,467 --> 01:32:41,972
YOU DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING TO DO
WITH WHAT DEL WAS INTO, DID YOU, BETTY ?

1419
01:32:41,973 --> 01:32:44,976
I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
DEL WAS MIXED UP IN.

1420
01:32:45,977 --> 01:32:48,980
SO... YOU HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH THE DRUGS.

1421
01:32:48,980 --> 01:32:53,985
OH, MY GOD.  DRUGS ?
GOD, NO !

1422
01:32:53,985 --> 01:32:56,988
I AM TOTALLY
AGAINST DRUGS.

1423
01:32:56,988 --> 01:32:59,490
[ Chuckles ]

1424
01:33:02,493 --> 01:33:04,495
LIFE IS VERY STRANGE.

1425
01:33:04,495 --> 01:33:09,500
I REALLY HAD YOU PEGGED
AS A COLD-BLOODED BITCH.

1426
01:33:10,001 --> 01:33:12,620
I MEAN, NOT THAT I DIDN'T
STILL ADMIRE YOU FOR IT.

1427
01:33:21,379 --> 01:33:23,881
<i>IF YOU DIDN'T</i>
<i>COME HERE TO KILL ME,</i> <i>THEN...</i>

1428
01:33:24,265 --> 01:33:27,635
WHY ARE YOU HERE ?

1429
01:33:31,138 --> 01:33:34,141
TO SEE YOU.

1430
01:33:34,141 --> 01:33:37,561
<i>NOW HOW'D YOU TWO</i>
<i>DUMB FUCKS FIND BETTY ?</i>

1431
01:33:37,561 --> 01:33:39,563
I JUST PUT IT ALL TOGETHER.

1432
01:33:39,563 --> 01:33:42,065
I KNEW THAT DAVID,
LONNIE AND CHLOE WERE FROM THAT SHOW.

1433
01:33:42,066 --> 01:33:45,569
- [ Muffled Yelling ]
- BETTY THINKS THEY'RE REAL PEOPLE.

1434
01:33:45,703 --> 01:33:48,455
SOUNDED STRANGE,
BUT IT WAS WORTH A SHOT.

1435
01:33:48,706 --> 01:33:50,708
- [ Continues Yelling ]
- WHAT DO YOU WANT ?

1436
01:33:50,708 --> 01:33:54,078
IGNORE HIM.
DON'T TAKE THAT TAPE OFF. YOU'RE GONNA REGRET IT.

1437
01:33:54,078 --> 01:33:56,830
YOU'RE SUCH A LIAR,
ELDEN BALLARD !

1438
01:33:57,081 --> 01:33:59,716
- OH, SHUT UP !
- LIAR !  I'M THE ONE THAT FIGURED IT OUT, NOT HIM !

1439
01:33:59,717 --> 01:34:02,720
- SHUT UP !
- YOU ARE REALLY SMART ! - FUCK YOU, ROY OSTREY.

1440
01:34:02,720 --> 01:34:04,972
- HEY, SHUT UP !
- <i>I'M THE ONE THAT WATCHED THE--</i> <i>- SHUT THE FUCK UP !</i>

1441
01:34:04,972 --> 01:34:08,225
SHUT THE FUCK UP
BOTH OF YOU BEFORE I KILL BOTH OF YOU !

1442
01:34:08,476 --> 01:34:11,095
- YOU WATCH THE SHOW ?
- YEAH, I'M THE ONE THAT WATCHED THE SHOW !

1443
01:34:11,095 --> 01:34:13,097
HE'S THE ONE THAT DIDN'T
'CAUSE HE'S A LIAR !

1444
01:34:13,097 --> 01:34:15,599
CALM DOWN !
STOP ACTING LIKE A LITTLE BITCH.

1445
01:34:16,100 --> 01:34:18,102
NOW, DID CHLOE CRACK ?

1446
01:34:18,102 --> 01:34:20,104
CHLOE FELL
COMPLETELY APART !

1447
01:34:20,104 --> 01:34:22,606
YOU DIDN'T KNOW CHLOE CRACKED,
DID YOU ? [ Screams ]

1448
01:34:22,606 --> 01:34:25,108
WHAT ABOUT JASMINE ?

1449
01:34:25,109 --> 01:34:27,611
- JASMINE'S A LESBIAN.
- LYIN' MOTHERFUCKER !

1450
01:34:27,611 --> 01:34:30,113
YOU LIE !
JASMINE IS NOT A LESBIAN !

1451
01:34:30,114 --> 01:34:31,615
I KNOW WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT !

1452
01:34:31,999 --> 01:34:33,750
[ Muffled Yelling ]
WHAT YOU WANT ?

1453
01:34:33,751 --> 01:34:36,253
YOU SCREAM, YOU DIE.
I'M GONNA TAKE THIS SHIT OFF.

1454
01:34:36,754 --> 01:34:39,256
YOU SCREAM,
YOU FUCKIN' DIE !

1455
01:34:39,256 --> 01:34:43,260
I HAVE A TAPE
OF TODAY'S SHOW.

1456
01:34:43,511 --> 01:34:45,513
[ Jasmine ]
YOU'VE GOT A LOT OF MEN IN MOTION OVER WHAT YOU DID.

1457
01:34:45,513 --> 01:34:48,516
<i>WHAT I DID ?</i>
<i>DON'T GIVE ME THAT,</i> <i>CHLOE.</i>

1458
01:34:48,516 --> 01:34:52,019
<i>WHAT ABOUT WHAT HE DID ?</i>
<i>I WASN'T BORN YESTERDAY.</i>

1459
01:34:52,019 --> 01:34:55,989
<i>YOU GET IN A MAN'S CAR,</i>
<i>THERE'S A REASON.</i> <i>WE BOTH KNOW THAT.</i>

1460
01:34:55,990 --> 01:34:58,809
DO YOU THINK
THAT MAYBE-- NO, NO.  THEY'RE FINE.

1461
01:34:59,193 --> 01:35:01,195
THEY'RE FINE.

1462
01:35:03,197 --> 01:35:06,200
I DON'T MEET PEOPLE LIKE YOU.

1463
01:35:06,200 --> 01:35:10,204
I'M A GARBAGEMAN
OF THE HUMAN CONDITION. I DEAL WITH TRASH.

1464
01:35:10,204 --> 01:35:14,208
PEOPLE WHO WOULD TRADE ANY PART
OF THEMSELVES FOR A FEW MORE MINUTES OF THEIR ROTTEN LIVES.

1465
01:35:14,709 --> 01:35:16,711
BUT YOU'RE DIFFERENT.

1466
01:35:16,711 --> 01:35:20,214
I AM ?
YEAH.

1467
01:35:20,214 --> 01:35:22,216
YOU COULD PROBABLY
HAVE ANYTHING YOU WANT.

1468
01:35:22,216 --> 01:35:25,719
AW.
SOMEBODY AS BEAUTIFUL AND AS STYLISH AS YOU ARE,

1469
01:35:25,720 --> 01:35:28,222
AND YOU DON'T EVEN
REALIZE IT.

1470
01:35:28,222 --> 01:35:31,225
I JUST DON'T THINK
I'M WHO YOU THINK I AM.

1471
01:35:31,726 --> 01:35:34,228
LOOK, LET ME JUST
GET THIS OUT.

1472
01:35:37,348 --> 01:35:41,852
I LIKE WALKS IN THE RAIN
AND SUNSETS AND SYMPHONIES,

1473
01:35:41,852 --> 01:35:44,354
KIDS, ANIMALS.

1474
01:35:44,355 --> 01:35:46,857
I READ PASSIONATELY.
I LIKE TO DISCUSS THINGS.

1475
01:35:46,857 --> 01:35:51,361
OH.
I GUESS, BASICALLY, I'M CONSERVATIVE,

1476
01:35:51,362 --> 01:35:53,864
BUT FLEXIBLE.

1477
01:35:56,367 --> 01:35:59,870
I FOLLOWED YOU
ALL THE WAY ACROSS THE COUNTRY, YOU KNOW,

1478
01:36:00,371 --> 01:36:03,874
AND I'VE COME
TO FEEL THAT...

1479
01:36:03,874 --> 01:36:07,377
WE'RE A LOT MORE ALIKE
THAN YOU THINK.

1480
01:36:07,378 --> 01:36:09,380
BUT I THOUGHT
YOU SAID...

1481
01:36:09,880 --> 01:36:13,884
THAT YOU WERE
THE GARBAGEMAN OF HUMANITY.

1482
01:36:13,884 --> 01:36:16,887
I JUST...

1483
01:36:16,887 --> 01:36:19,890
HOPED I COULD LEAVE THAT
BEHIND ME.

1484
01:36:22,893 --> 01:36:25,729
I THOUGHT "NO" MEANT NO.

1485
01:36:25,863 --> 01:36:29,867
<i>[ Jasmine Scoffs ]</i>
<i>[ Chloe ]</i> <i>WHAT ?</i>

1486
01:36:29,867 --> 01:36:33,370
<i>SAY SOMETHING.</i>

1487
01:36:33,370 --> 01:36:36,873
FIRST OF ALL,
DON'T INSULT MY INTELLIGENCE...

1488
01:36:37,374 --> 01:36:40,377
BY TELLING ME
THAT DAVID RAVELL ATTACKED YOU IN THAT CAR.

1489
01:36:40,377 --> 01:36:44,381
SO, UM, THAT JASMINE,
SHE'S CERTAINLY IS INTRIGUING, ISN'T SHE ?

1490
01:36:44,381 --> 01:36:49,753
JASMINE AIN'T NO DYKE.
SHE'S JUST TRYIN' TO FIND HERSELF.

1491
01:36:50,137 --> 01:36:53,256
- YOU'RE MY ONLY FRIEND.
- LOOK AT THE TITTIES ON JASMINE.

1492
01:36:53,257 --> 01:36:56,009
[ TV Continues, Indistinct ]

1493
01:36:56,010 --> 01:36:59,263
<i>[ Wesley ]</i>
<i>GODDAMN !</i> <i>AH, SUKI, SUKI, NOW.</i>

1494
01:36:59,263 --> 01:37:02,266
<i>LOOK AT THAT !</i>
<i>YOU CAN DO THAT SHIT</i> <i>ON TV ?  OH, SHIT !</i>

1495
01:37:02,266 --> 01:37:05,269
<i>LOOK AT THAT SHIT !</i>

1496
01:37:05,269 --> 01:37:08,772
JASMINE IS A WILDCAT.
YOU WOULD NEVER COOK UP A SCHEME LIKE THIS, WOULD YOU ?

1497
01:37:10,908 --> 01:37:13,410
WHAT THE--  OH, SHIT !

1498
01:37:21,669 --> 01:37:24,171
- [ Screams ]
- WESLEY ! GET OVER THERE.

1499
01:37:24,421 --> 01:37:26,923
[ Groaning ]

1500
01:37:27,174 --> 01:37:28,925
DADDY !

1501
01:37:29,927 --> 01:37:31,929
WHAT ?  WESLEY ?

1502
01:37:43,190 --> 01:37:45,192
OH, MY GOD !
MY FISH ARE OUT THERE !

1503
01:37:45,693 --> 01:37:48,696
I KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW.
THEY'RE NISHIKI GOI. HOW'D YOU KNOW THAT ?

1504
01:37:48,812 --> 01:37:52,315
HEY, WE'RE IN A SHOOT-OUT HERE !
YOU WANNA SHUT UP ABOUT THE DAMN FISH ?

1505
01:37:52,566 --> 01:37:54,951
NO, ELDEN !
YOU SHUT UP !

1506
01:37:55,452 --> 01:37:58,455
I'LL GET YOUR FISH.

1507
01:37:58,455 --> 01:37:59,956
ROY.

1508
01:37:59,957 --> 01:38:02,960
OH, CHRIST.
[ Betty ] WHAT ?

1509
01:38:04,962 --> 01:38:09,466
TH--  THEY--
THEY SHOT MY BOY.

1510
01:38:14,972 --> 01:38:17,474
MY SON IS DEAD.

1511
01:38:17,474 --> 01:38:19,976
SORRY.

1512
01:38:22,980 --> 01:38:25,349
YOU'RE THE REASON
I'M HERE.

1513
01:38:25,349 --> 01:38:28,352
<i>THAT'S RIGHT.</i>
<i>I'M HERE BECAUSE OF YOU.</i>

1514
01:38:28,352 --> 01:38:31,355
OH.

1515
01:38:33,357 --> 01:38:35,359
OHH !

1516
01:38:55,512 --> 01:38:57,514
SHIT.

1517
01:38:59,967 --> 01:39:01,768
<i>[ Elden ]</i>
<i>I NEED MY OTHER GUN.</i>

1518
01:39:01,769 --> 01:39:03,270
GO CHECK HIS JACKET.
GIVE ME THE GUN. I'LL COVER YOU.

1519
01:39:03,270 --> 01:39:06,273
- NO.  LET'S WAIT
FOR THE REAL POLICE. - I AM THE REAL POLICE !

1520
01:39:06,774 --> 01:39:10,778
- WHY CAN'T WE SNEAK OUTSIDE ?
- LADY, YOU JUST DON'T RUN AWAY FROM CRIME.

1521
01:39:10,778 --> 01:39:13,280
AND BETTY'S IN THERE.

1522
01:39:18,402 --> 01:39:21,405
SO ALL OF THIS REALLY IS
BECAUSE OF A SOAP OPERA.

1523
01:39:21,405 --> 01:39:24,791
MY SON IS DEAD BECAUSE...

1524
01:39:26,794 --> 01:39:29,296
YOU WANTED TO BE
WITH THIS DOCTOR.

1525
01:39:29,797 --> 01:39:32,916
THIS FAKE DOCTOR.

1526
01:39:32,916 --> 01:39:38,922
[ Sirens Wailing ]

1527
01:39:38,922 --> 01:39:42,425
WELL, TOO LATE ANYWAY.

1528
01:39:42,426 --> 01:39:44,561
YOU COULD AT LEAST
GIVE ME MY GUN.

1529
01:39:44,561 --> 01:39:48,064
MAYBE I COULD SHOOT MY WAY OUT,
TAKE A COUPLE OF THEM WITH ME.

1530
01:39:48,065 --> 01:39:51,435
I THINK I'D RATHER NOT.

1531
01:39:51,568 --> 01:39:54,070
BETTY, PLEASE.  PLEASE.

1532
01:39:54,071 --> 01:39:58,575
I DON'T WANNA SHRIVEL UP ALONE
IN SOME STINKIN' PRISON. NO WAY.

1533
01:39:58,575 --> 01:40:01,077
I'VE GOT
MY PROFESSIONAL PRIDE.

1534
01:40:01,195 --> 01:40:03,447
AND...

1535
01:40:04,948 --> 01:40:09,702
I DON'T WANT SOMEBODY ELSE
TO GET CREDIT FOR TAKING ME OUT.

1536
01:40:13,590 --> 01:40:16,092
I WANT YOU TO LISTEN TO ME.

1537
01:40:20,097 --> 01:40:22,599
BETTY--

1538
01:40:25,102 --> 01:40:28,105
YOU NEVER NEEDED
THAT ACTOR.

1539
01:40:28,105 --> 01:40:30,607
YOU DON'T NEED
THAT DOCTOR.

1540
01:40:30,607 --> 01:40:33,109
YOU DON'T NEED ANY MAN.

1541
01:40:33,110 --> 01:40:36,113
IT'S NOT THE '40s,
YOU KNOW.

1542
01:40:36,113 --> 01:40:39,616
HONEY,
YOU DON'T NEED ANYBODY.

1543
01:40:39,616 --> 01:40:42,118
YOU KNOW WHY ?

1544
01:40:42,119 --> 01:40:44,121
HMM ?

1545
01:40:49,126 --> 01:40:52,496
'CAUSE YOU'VE GOT
YOURSELF.

1546
01:41:42,930 --> 01:41:44,932
<i>[ Gunshot ]</i>
<i>[ Sirens Wailing ]</i>

1547
01:41:45,432 --> 01:41:49,552
[ Anchorwoman ]
IN A STORY THAT POLICE SAY IS BIZARRE EVEN FOR HOLLYWOOD,

1548
01:41:49,553 --> 01:41:51,555
A FATHER-SON TEAM
OF KILLERS...

1549
01:41:51,555 --> 01:41:55,559
TRACKED A KANSAS SOAP OPERA FAN
HALFWAY ACROSS THE COUNTRY,

1550
01:41:55,559 --> 01:42:00,564
ONLY TO FIND THEMSELVES
THE VICTIMS IN A FINAL, BLOODY CONFRONTATION.

1551
01:42:00,564 --> 01:42:02,566
WE GO NOW TO BEBE BURKE
AT THE SCENE OF THE-- THAT'S OUR BETTY.

1552
01:42:02,566 --> 01:42:06,570
THIS STORY
IS BEYOND BELIEF, WHICH IS PERFECT FOR US.

1553
01:42:06,570 --> 01:42:09,072
IT'S FREE ADVERTISING.
IT'S GONNA RUN FOR MONTHS.

1554
01:42:09,072 --> 01:42:11,574
I DON'T THINK
SHE CAN DO IT.

1555
01:42:11,825 --> 01:42:14,327
I REALLY DON'T.
ARE YOU SERIOUS ?

1556
01:42:14,328 --> 01:42:17,331
DID YOU SEE WHAT HAPPENED ?
WELL, WHO WOULDN'T FREEZE UNDER THOSE CIRCUMSTANCES ?

1557
01:42:17,331 --> 01:42:19,333
AND I DON'T CARE
WHAT HER PROBLEMS ARE.

1558
01:42:19,333 --> 01:42:21,835
SHE WOULDN'T BE
THE FIRST PERSON IN THE CAST WITH PROBLEMS.

1559
01:42:21,835 --> 01:42:25,839
THAT'S WHY WE HAVE
NOTHING TO LOSE BY SENDING YOU TO TALK TO HER.

1560
01:42:26,340 --> 01:42:29,343
ME ?  OKAY.
LET'S TALK ABOUT ME.

1561
01:42:29,343 --> 01:42:31,845
WHAT ABOUT MY FEELINGS
ABOUT ALL OF THIS ?

1562
01:42:31,845 --> 01:42:33,847
I DON'T REALLY CARE
ABOUT YOUR FEELINGS. [ Laughs ]

1563
01:42:33,847 --> 01:42:36,850
I DID LIKE
YOUR ICY WATER IDEA THE OTHER DAY THOUGH.

1564
01:42:36,850 --> 01:42:39,853
YEAH ?

1565
01:42:39,853 --> 01:42:43,356
I'M TOYING WITH THE IDEA
OF KILLING DAVID RAVELL OFF...

1566
01:42:43,857 --> 01:42:45,859
IN A BOATING ACCIDENT.

1567
01:42:45,859 --> 01:42:48,361
ONE OF THOSE
CASTAWAY DEALS WITH CHLOE AND--

1568
01:42:48,362 --> 01:42:53,367
<i>NO ?</i>
<i>HOW DO I COME BACK ?</i>

1569
01:42:53,367 --> 01:42:57,871
NO, NO, NO.  DON'T--
DON'T TRY THE BLACKMAIL BULLSHIT WITH ME, LYLA,

1570
01:42:57,871 --> 01:43:00,373
'CAUSE IT'S KINDA,
IT'S BENEATH YOU, SO DON'T EVEN THINK ABOUT IT.

1571
01:43:00,874 --> 01:43:04,878
<i>IT'S AN EMPHATIC NO,</i>
<i>MISSY.  POOM !</i> <i>END OF STORY RIGHT THERE.</i>

1572
01:43:07,014 --> 01:43:09,016
I'M SORRY
FOR WHAT I DID.

1573
01:43:09,016 --> 01:43:13,887
I'M SORRY FOR THE THINGS
THAT I SAID AND...

1574
01:43:13,887 --> 01:43:17,390
FOR NOT
RESPECTING YOU...

1575
01:43:17,391 --> 01:43:22,279
AND JUST ALL THE STUPID
LITTLE THINGS THAT I WAS--

1576
01:43:22,279 --> 01:43:25,282
WHEN YOU HAVE A MINUTE.
I REALLY DON'T LIKE THE IDEA OF AUTOGRAPHS,

1577
01:43:25,532 --> 01:43:27,534
AND I'M KIND OF
IN A MOMENT RIGHT HERE, SO--

1578
01:43:27,784 --> 01:43:29,285
IT'S THE CHECK.

1579
01:43:29,286 --> 01:43:32,789
[ Clears Throat ]
I--  SORRY ABOUT THAT.

1580
01:43:33,290 --> 01:43:36,293
UH--  NO.  I GOT THIS.
I GOT THIS.

1581
01:43:36,293 --> 01:43:38,295
MY TREAT.

1582
01:43:38,295 --> 01:43:41,798
IT'S NOT THE '40s,
YOU KNOW.

1583
01:43:41,798 --> 01:43:44,300
OKAY.
[ Chuckles ]

1584
01:43:44,301 --> 01:43:46,803
YOU KNOW THAT MY BEST FRIEND
ONCE SAID...

1585
01:43:46,803 --> 01:43:50,807
THAT IF YOU WERE
ANY HANDSOMER, IT'D BE A CRIME ?

1586
01:43:50,807 --> 01:43:55,311
THANK YOU.
IT'S JUST TOO BAD THAT YOU'RE SUCH AN ASSHOLE.

1587
01:43:58,815 --> 01:44:01,818
UH, THAT'S OKAY.
YOU KNOW WHAT ? THAT'S OKAY.

1588
01:44:01,818 --> 01:44:05,321
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'M OKAY WITH THAT. THAT'S FAIR ENOUGH.

1589
01:44:05,322 --> 01:44:11,328
NOW WE'VE SETTLED
THE WHOLE ASSHOLE THING, WELL--

1590
01:44:11,328 --> 01:44:16,333
IS THERE ANY CHANCE THAT
YOU WOULD THINK ABOUT JOINING THE SHOW ?

1591
01:44:21,838 --> 01:44:24,340
AT ALL ?

1592
01:44:24,341 --> 01:44:27,377
THERE'S ALWAYS
A CHANCE, DAVID.

1593
01:44:27,377 --> 01:44:29,379
BUT WHAT ABOUT TOMORROW
AND THE NEXT DAY...

1594
01:44:29,379 --> 01:44:31,881
<i>AND THE NEXT DAY</i>
<i>AND THE NEXT ?</i>

1595
01:44:31,882 --> 01:44:37,387
IF YOU WERE
ANY HANDSOMER, DOCTOR, IT'D BE A CRIME.

1596
01:44:37,387 --> 01:44:40,390
I TAKE IT THAT MEANS
YOU'RE FREE TOMORROW.

1597
01:44:40,390 --> 01:44:43,393
I WAS GOING
TO ASK YOU THAT TOO.

1598
01:44:43,393 --> 01:44:46,779
<i>IT'S AS IF I'VE BEEN IN</i>
<i>SOME SORT OF DREAM STATE.</i>

1599
01:44:46,780 --> 01:44:52,285
LIKE--  LIKE YOU
DIDN'T KNOW WHO YOU WERE OR WHAT YOU WERE DOING ?

1600
01:44:52,286 --> 01:44:55,405
- <i>YES.</i>
<i>-</i> <i>[ Speaking Spanish ]</i>

1601
01:44:55,405 --> 01:44:57,407
I HAVE THAT EFFECT
ON PEOPLE.

1602
01:44:57,407 --> 01:45:00,660
<i>WELL, YOU CERTAINLY</i>
<i>HAD THAT EFFECT ON ME.</i>

1603
01:45:01,161 --> 01:45:07,167
[ Speaking Italian ]

1604
01:45:07,417 --> 01:45:09,669
<i>[ Continues ]</i>

1605
01:45:24,935 --> 01:45:26,937
EXCUSE ME, SIR ?

1606
01:45:26,937 --> 01:45:29,439
[ Bells Chiming ]

1607
01:45:29,439 --> 01:45:31,441
SIR ?

1608
01:46:24,745 --> 01:46:29,699
♪

1609
01:46:29,699 --> 01:46:33,703
